ysis blob produced by Claude during the slash command run. It renders sections (Overview, Tech Stack, Architecture with Mermaid, Algorithms, Methodologies, Pattern Rationale, Pitfalls, Glossary, Quiz), with each section carrying both technical and layman text variants.\n\n# Your Task\n\nGenerate contracts for these 2 Layer 1 components and write each one to `.framework/contracts/data/{ComponentName}.contract.md` (absolute paths under /Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing/).\n\n```yaml\ncomponents:\n  - name: AnalysisSchema\n    responsibility: \"Defines the canonical JSON shape Claude must emit when analyzing a project, with field-level docs and required/optional flags\"\n    owns:\n      - schema/analysis.schema.json\n      - schema/README.md\n    key_complexity: \"Capturing the dual technical/layman variants and Mermaid diagram source in a JSON schema that is strict enough to validate yet permissive enough for any stack\"\n    dependencies: []\n  - name: StackDetectionRules\n    responsibility: \"Lists manifest filenames per stack (package.json, pyproject.toml, Cargo.toml, pubspec.yaml, go.mod, etc.) and which secondary files to prioritize for reading\"\n    owns:\n      - schema/stack-detection.json\n    key_complexity: \"Covering enough stacks to be useful without becoming a brittle catalog; degrading gracefully when no manifest matches\"\n    dependencies: []\n```\n\n# Contract Template (data)\n\nUse this exact structure. Adapt sections that don't apply (e.g., this is a static JSON schema, not a database — replace \"Schema / Storage\" with \"JSON Schema Definition\", replace \"Data Access Methods\" with \"Consumer Access Patterns\", omit \"State Provider\" and replace with \"Distribution\" — how the consumer reads the schema file).\n\n```\n# {ComponentName} Contract\n\nLayer: data\n\n## Responsibility\n\n{One sentence}\n\n## JSON Schema Definition\n\n{Full JSON Schema (draft 2020-12) for the data this component owns. For AnalysisSchema, this is the schema for the analysis JSON. For StackDetectionRules, this is the schema for the stack-detection rules file PLUS the actual content. Include every field with type, required/optional, and one-line doc.}\n\n## Consumer Access Patterns\n\n### {access_pattern_name}\n- **Reader**: {who reads this — SlashCommand, LauncherScript, InteractiveJS}\n- **How**: {file path, fetch, fs.readFile, embedded in HTML, etc.}\n- **Behavior**: {what the reader does with it}\n- **Edge cases**: {list}\n\n[Repeat for each consumer]\n\n## Domain Model\n\n{Concrete TypeScript-style type definitions for the data shapes — e.g., interface AnalysisSection, interface TechStackEntry. Include defaults and required vs optional. JS is the runtime; type definitions are documentation only.}\n\n## Distribution\n\n- **Format**: JSON file shipped with the plugin\n- **Path in plugin**: {schema/analysis.schema.json or schema/stack-detection.json}\n- **Versioning**: {how breaking changes are signaled — e.g., $schemaVersion field}\n- **Cache strategy**: {N/A for static, or describe}\n\n## Dependencies\n\nNone. (Layer 1 components have no dependencies on other components.)\n\n## Test Requirements\n\n- [ ] JSON file is valid JSON\n- [ ] {component-specific tests, e.g., \"schema validates against a known-good fixture\", \"every documented stack has at least one manifest pattern\"}\n- [ ] {edge cases}\n```\n\n# Critical Requirements\n\n1. For AnalysisSchema: define the FULL JSON Schema that Claude must produce. Sections must include all listed in the project plan (overview, tech_stack, architecture, algorithms, methodologies, pattern_rationale, pitfalls, glossary, quiz). Every section should have BOTH a `technical` text field and a `layman` text field. Architecture must include `mermaid` (string of mermaid source). Glossary is array of {term, layman, technical}. Quiz is array of {question, choices[], answerIndex, explanation_layman, explanation_technical}.\n\n2. For StackDetectionRules: define the schema, then ALSO inline the actual rules content for these stacks at minimum: Node.js (package.json), Python (pyproject.toml, requirements.txt, setup.py), Rust (Cargo.toml), Go (go.mod), Flutter/Dart (pubspec.yaml), Java (pom.xml, build.gradle), Ruby (Gemfile), PHP (composer.json), .NET (*.csproj), Swift (Package.swift), plus a `unknown` fallback. Each rule entry must include: `manifestFiles` (priority-ordered list), `keyConfigFiles` (e.g., tsconfig.json, .eslintrc), `entryPointHints` (e.g., src/index.*, main.py), and `humanName` (e.g., \"Node.js / JavaScript\").\n\n3. Type definitions in Domain Model: use TypeScript-style interfaces — the project is JS/HTML, so TypeScript syntax is the natural type documentation language even though there's no compile step.\n\n4. Be exhaustive on edge cases: empty fields, monorepo with multiple manifests, no manifest at all, very large analysis, missing diagram source, glossary terms with no technical variant, etc.\n\n5. Write each contract as a separate file. Do not overwrite existing files (none should exist yet).\n\n# Deliverables\n\n- `/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing/.framework/contracts/data/AnalysisSchema.contract.md`\n- `/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing/.framework/contracts/data/StackDetectionRules.contract.md`\n\nReport back: file paths written, brief summary of key types defined, any open questions you flagged in the contracts.","outputFile":"/private/tmp/claude-501/-Users-avinkrism4pro-Personal-apps-MyApps-whatAmIDoing/85635977-a88f-4f4a-8a0a-ca947997bc25/tasks/acb6a84e4f165ffaf.output","canReadOutputFile":true},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"4bd44450-3ce1-44a7-8974-9565be675443","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing","sessionId":"72a03414-ba52-4106-b27a-7f28ae50fe45","version":"2.1.126","gitBranch":"main"}
{"parentUuid":"6e65172b-50d3-4b82-864d-fbcae651ecb0","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01181mqu7TRAH6Prn7rNHVsT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_018sPQDEz6xASFH8dzQiDrZd","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Generate L2 UI contracts","subagent_type":"general-purpose","model":"sonnet","prompt":"You are generating Trellis Phase 2 contracts for the Layer 2 (UI) components of the `waid-commands` Claude Code plugin.\n\n# Context\n\nThe plugin's purpose: a Claude Code slash command `/under-the-hood` that analyzes the current project and produces a self-contained HTML report teaching the user about their project's tech stack, architecture, methodologies, and pitfalls — with parallel Technical and Layman views.\n\nTech stack: `bash + markdown + html + css + javascript`. No build tooling. No server. Output is a single HTML file (assets/template.html with placeholder for analysis JSON; the launcher script substitutes the JSON in).\n\nSingle screen (`UnderTheHoodReport`) — sections: Overview, Tech Stack, Architecture (Mermaid), Algorithms, Methodologies, Pattern Rationale, Pitfalls, Glossary, Quiz. View toggle (Technical ↔ Layman). Theme toggle (light/dark). Sticky TOC, collapsible sections, glossary tooltips.\n\nThe analysis JSON shape is being defined by the data-agent in parallel (AnalysisSchema). For UI contract purposes, assume it has top-level fields:\n- `meta`: { generated_at: string, project_name: string, project_root: string, schema_version: string }\n- `overview`: { technical: string, layman: string }\n- `tech_stack`: TechStackEntry[]    // each has { name, kind, technical, layman, analogy?, version? }\n- `architecture`: { technical: string, layman: string, mermaid: string }\n- `algorithms`: AlgoEntry[]         // each has { name, technical, layman, complexity?, location? }\n- `methodologies`: MethodEntry[]    // each has { name, technical, layman }\n- `pattern_rationale`: PatternEntry[]  // each has { pattern, why, tradeoffs, technical, layman }\n- `pitfalls`: PitfallEntry[]        // each has { title, technical, layman, severity }\n- `glossary`: GlossaryEntry[]       // each has { term, layman, technical }\n- `quiz`: QuizEntry[]               // each has { question, choices: string[], answerIndex: number, explanation_layman, explanation_technical }\n\n# Your Task\n\nGenerate contracts for these 2 Layer 2 components and write each one to a separate file under `/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing/.framework/contracts/ui/`:\n\n```yaml\ncomponents:\n  - name: HtmlTemplate\n    responsibility: \"Single self-contained HTML shell with placeholder for analysis JSON; renders all sections + view-toggle / TOC / theme-toggle chrome\"\n    owns:\n      - assets/template.html\n    key_complexity: \"Keeping it self-contained (no build step) while supporting Mermaid (CDN), conditional rendering of technical vs layman text, and graceful empty-section handling\"\n    dependencies: []\n  - name: InteractiveJS\n    responsibility: \"Inline JavaScript for the report — view toggle, theme toggle, TOC scroll-spy, glossary tooltips, section collapse, Mermaid init, quiz logic, JSON-into-DOM render\"\n    owns:\n      - assets/template.js\n    key_complexity: \"Rendering arbitrary analysis JSON safely (no XSS), and wiring view/theme state to localStorage with a sensible default\"\n    dependencies: []\n```\n\n# Contract Template (ui)\n\nAdapt this for static HTML/JS components (no React-style props/callbacks; instead, document the placeholder substitution contract for HtmlTemplate, and the public function/event contract for InteractiveJS):\n\n```\n# {ComponentName} Contract\n\nLayer: ui\n\n## Responsibility\n\n{One sentence}\n\n## Substitution / API Contract\n\nFor HtmlTemplate: list every placeholder string that the launcher substitutes (e.g., `__WAID_ANALYSIS_JSON__`, `__WAID_TEMPLATE_CSS__`, `__WAID_TEMPLATE_JS__`, `__WAID_GENERATED_AT__`). For each: where in the HTML it appears, what shape the substituted value must have, and what happens if the substitution fails.\n\nFor InteractiveJS: list the global function/object exposed (e.g., `window.WAID.init(analysisJson)`), public events emitted (custom DOM events), and any DOM contract (required element IDs / classes).\n\n| Item | Type | Required | Default | Purpose |\n|------|------|----------|---------|---------|\n\n## Visual / Behavior\n\n- **Default state**: {what renders before any user interaction — both modes}\n- **Loading state**: {N/A for static; or \"JSON not yet substituted\" failure mode}\n- **Empty state**: {when a section in the JSON is empty array — the section should hide or show \"—\" placeholder; specify}\n- **Error state**: {what happens if analysisJson is malformed; if Mermaid CDN fails to load}\n- **Animations**: {transition-on-toggle, accordion expand/collapse, scroll-snap}\n- **Interactions**: {click TOC, click section header to collapse, hover glossary term, click quiz choice, view/theme toggle}\n\n## Sizing / Layout\n\n{Describe page layout: max-width content column, sticky TOC sidebar on >=lg, stacked on mobile. Responsive breakpoints. Print-friendliness.}\n\n## Theme Dependency\n\n{Token names from DesignTokens contract that this component consumes — e.g., --waid-color-bg, --waid-color-fg, --waid-color-accent, --waid-font-body, --waid-font-mono, --waid-space-1..8, --waid-radius-md, --waid-shadow-card. Reference TOKENS, not raw values.}\n\n## Test Requirements\n\n- [ ] Renders correctly with full fixture analysis JSON\n- [ ] Handles edge values: empty sections, very long text, single-character glossary term\n- [ ] View toggle persists across reload (localStorage)\n- [ ] Theme toggle persists across reload (localStorage)\n- [ ] No XSS: HTML inside analysis text is escaped\n- [ ] Mermaid CDN failure does not break the page\n- [ ] Works offline if Mermaid is the only network dep\n```\n\n# Critical Requirements\n\n1. **HtmlTemplate** is a static `.html` file with placeholder tokens. Document EVERY placeholder using the format `__WAID_FOO__` and what gets substituted in.\n2. **InteractiveJS** is a single `.js` file embedded by the template. It must:\n   - Expose `window.WAID` with `init(analysisJson)` (idempotent), `setView('technical' | 'layman')`, `setTheme('light' | 'dark' | 'auto')`.\n   - Render JSON to DOM by template cloning (use `<template>` elements in the HTML), not innerHTML on user-content strings.\n   - Hydrate Mermaid only after the architecture section is rendered.\n   - Persist `waid-view` and `waid-theme` in localStorage.\n   - Initialize quiz state, evaluate answers locally, never network.\n3. Theme tokens listed must be consistent across both contracts (use the same names — keep a list).\n4. Be specific about DOM IDs / classes that the launcher or other components need to know about. For example: `#waid-root`, `#waid-toc`, `#waid-view-toggle`, `#waid-theme-toggle`, sections with `data-waid-section=\"overview\"`, etc.\n\n# Deliverables\n\n- `/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing/.framework/contracts/ui/HtmlTemplate.contract.md`\n- `/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing/.framework/contracts/ui/InteractiveJS.contract.md`\n\nReport back: file paths written, list of placeholder tokens, list of DOM IDs/classes, list of theme tokens consumed.","run_in_background":true},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":817,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1449,"cache_read_input_tokens":54691,"output_tokens":11103,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1449,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":817,"output_tokens":11103,"cache_read_input_tokens":54691,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1449,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens"