{"parentUuid":"ae2e8b27-0ddd-43ae-ba2c-dd7703ace8ad","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01181mqu7TRAH6Prn7rNHVsT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01LU3Z9dJ5Y4U1DowMqnpUCM","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Generate L3 logic contracts","subagent_type":"general-purpose","model":"sonnet","prompt":"You are generating Trellis Phase 2 contracts for the Layer 3 (Logic) components of the `waid-commands` Claude Code plugin.\n\n# Context\n\n`waid-commands` is a Claude Code plugin. The slash command `/under-the-hood` instructs Claude (running in the user's Claude Code session) to scan the user's current project, produce a JSON analysis conforming to AnalysisSchema, then invoke a launcher script that injects the JSON into an HTML template and opens the result in the user's default browser.\n\nTech stack: `bash + markdown + html + css + javascript`. No build tools.\n\nThe flow when user types `/under-the-hood`:\n1. Claude Code loads `commands/under-the-hood.md` content as a prompt.\n2. Following the prompt, Claude detects the project's stack via StackDetectionRules, reads relevant files, and writes `analysis.json` to a temp path.\n3. Claude calls `scripts/launch.sh <analysis.json> [--out=path] [--no-open]`.\n4. `launch.sh` reads template.html / template.css / template.js, substitutes placeholders, writes `under-the-hood.html` to the project root, opens it in the default browser.\n\nComponents in other layers (already known):\n- AnalysisSchema (data) — defines the JSON shape Claude must emit\n- StackDetectionRules (data) — manifest patterns + key file hints per stack, file: `schema/stack-detection.json`\n- HtmlTemplate (ui) — `assets/template.html` with placeholders `__WAID_ANALYSIS_JSON__`, `__WAID_TEMPLATE_CSS__`, `__WAID_TEMPLATE_JS__`, `__WAID_GENERATED_AT__`\n- InteractiveJS (ui) — `assets/template.js`, exposes `window.WAID.init(analysisJson)`\n- DesignTokens (theme) — `assets/template.css`\n\n# Your Task\n\nGenerate contracts for these 2 Layer 3 components and write each one to a separate file under `/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing/.framework/contracts/logic/`:\n\n```yaml\ncomponents:\n  - name: SlashCommand\n    responsibility: \"The /under-the-hood Claude Code slash command — a markdown prompt that instructs Claude how to scan the project, what files to read, what JSON shape to emit, and how to invoke the launcher\"\n    owns:\n      - commands/under-the-hood.md\n    key_complexity: \"Writing a prompt that produces consistent JSON conforming to AnalysisSchema across diverse stacks, with clear technical/layman variants and accurate Mermaid diagrams\"\n    dependencies: [AnalysisSchema, StackDetectionRules]\n  - name: LauncherScript\n    responsibility: \"Bash script that takes the analysis JSON path, injects it into the HTML template, writes ./under-the-hood.html, and opens it in the default browser (cross-platform: open / xdg-open / start)\"\n    owns:\n      - scripts/launch.sh\n    key_complexity: \"Cross-platform open command + safe JSON-into-HTML injection (no shell escaping bugs, no template-string collisions)\"\n    dependencies: [AnalysisSchema]\n```\n\n# Contract Template (logic)\n\nAdapt for the two non-traditional shapes — SlashCommand is a markdown prompt (its \"state\" is the analysis it tells Claude to produce; its \"methods\" are the steps the prompt prescribes); LauncherScript is a CLI script (its \"methods\" are CLI invocations; its \"state\" is filesystem):\n\n```\n# {ComponentName} Contract\n\nLayer: logic\n\n## Responsibility\n\n{One sentence}\n\n## Inputs\n\nFor SlashCommand: what triggers it (user types `/under-the-hood [optional args]`), arguments accepted, the project context Claude has access to.\nFor LauncherScript: positional/flag arguments, env vars consulted (e.g., $BROWSER), files it expects to find relative to the plugin root.\n\n| Input | Type | Required | Default | Purpose |\n|-------|------|----------|---------|---------|\n\n## Procedure / Methods\n\n### {step or subcommand name}\n- **Signature**: {how it's invoked or which prompt section governs}\n- **Behavior**: {step-by-step what happens}\n- **Side effects**: {file writes, browser launches, stdout, etc.}\n- **Edge cases**: {list}\n\n[Repeat for each step or method]\n\n## Outputs\n\n| Output | Type | When |\n|--------|------|------|\n\n## Error Handling\n\n{For each known failure: detection, message format, exit code, recovery hint to the user.}\n\n## Dependencies\n\n{Layer 1 data components consumed: AnalysisSchema, StackDetectionRules. Plus environment dependencies — bash version, jq presence, sed/awk usage, Python fallback if available, etc.}\n\n## Test Requirements\n\n- [ ] {component-specific cases}\n```\n\n# Critical Requirements for SlashCommand\n\n1. The contract must spell out the procedure Claude follows when the slash command runs. Include:\n   - Step 1: read `schema/stack-detection.json`, glob the project root for matching manifest files\n   - Step 2: read top-level files (~10–20), config files relevant to detected stack, entry points, and a sample of source files (cap to ~30 files total)\n   - Step 3: produce JSON conforming to `schema/analysis.schema.json`. Both technical AND layman text for every section.\n   - Step 4: write JSON to `${TMPDIR:-/tmp}/waid-analysis-$$.json`\n   - Step 5: invoke `scripts/launch.sh \"$JSON_PATH\"`. Handle non-zero exit by reporting to the user.\n   - Step 6: report a one-line success message with the output path.\n2. Argument shape: `/under-the-hood [--depth=quick|standard|deep] [--mode=technical|layman|both] [--out=path] [--no-open]`. Document each.\n3. Token budget guidance: cap files read so total context stays under ~50k tokens.\n4. Quality bar for each section's content (length, what makes a good Mermaid diagram, how to write a good layman analogy).\n5. Privacy: never network (no API calls, no telemetry); the analysis stays local.\n\n# Critical Requirements for LauncherScript\n\n1. **CLI signature**: `scripts/launch.sh <analysis.json> [--out=PATH] [--no-open] [--template-dir=PATH]`\n2. **Substitution method**: must be safe against arbitrary JSON content. Recommend reading the JSON file and embedding via a placeholder marker, using a delimiter no JSON content can contain (e.g., a UUID-tagged sentinel) and `awk`/`python3 -c` rather than `sed` (sed is unsafe with arbitrary content).\n3. **Required substitutions** in template.html: `__WAID_ANALYSIS_JSON__` (raw JSON value), `__WAID_TEMPLATE_CSS__` (entire CSS file content), `__WAID_TEMPLATE_JS__` (entire JS file content), `__WAID_GENERATED_AT__` (ISO 8601 timestamp).\n4. **Output path**: default `./under-the-hood.html` in CWD; overridable via `--out`. Must NOT clobber a directory.\n5. **Open command**: `open` on macOS, `xdg-open` on Linux, `start` on Windows (Git Bash detects via $OSTYPE or `uname`). `--no-open` skips this. Failure to open should warn but not fail (HTML is still written).\n6. **Exit codes**: 0 on success, 1 on missing input/template, 2 on substitution failure, 3 on open failure (non-fatal — warning only).\n7. **Determinism**: same input JSON should produce byte-identical HTML output (timestamp goes in a specific placeholder, not embedded into the JSON).\n8. **No bashisms beyond bash 3.2** (macOS default); document if anything requires bash 4+.\n\n# Deliverables\n\n- `/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing/.framework/contracts/logic/SlashCommand.contract.md`\n- `/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing/.framework/contracts/logic/LauncherScript.contract.md`\n\nReport back: file paths written, the slash command argument signature, the launcher CLI signature, list of required placeholder substitutions.","run_in_background":true},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":817,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1449,"cache_read_input_tokens":54691,"output_token