des**: 0 on success, 1 on missing input/template, 2 on substitution failure, 3 on open failure (non-fatal — warning only).\n7. **Determinism**: same input JSON should produce byte-identical HTML output (timestamp goes in a specific placeholder, not embedded into the JSON).\n8. **No bashisms beyond bash 3.2** (macOS default); document if anything requires bash 4+.\n\n# Deliverables\n\n- `/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing/.framework/contracts/logic/SlashCommand.contract.md`\n- `/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing/.framework/contracts/logic/LauncherScript.contract.md`\n\nReport back: file paths written, the slash command argument signature, the launcher CLI signature, list of required placeholder substitutions.","outputFile":"/private/tmp/claude-501/-Users-avinkrism4pro-Personal-apps-MyApps-whatAmIDoing/85635977-a88f-4f4a-8a0a-ca947997bc25/tasks/a78101c9db3f3982c.output","canReadOutputFile":true},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"2804f7f9-8129-4013-ad41-d36a4e5cbd87","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing","sessionId":"72a03414-ba52-4106-b27a-7f28ae50fe45","version":"2.1.126","gitBranch":"main"}
{"parentUuid":"f9085015-1e5d-4362-b447-76d87f118273","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01181mqu7TRAH6Prn7rNHVsT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_016cbjpKHm8zaARo4JPt8Aok","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Generate L4 theme contract","subagent_type":"general-purpose","model":"sonnet","prompt":"You are generating Trellis Phase 2 contract for the Layer 4 (Theme) component of the `waid-commands` Claude Code plugin.\n\n# Context\n\n`waid-commands` is a Claude Code plugin. Its slash command `/under-the-hood` produces a self-contained HTML report. The HTML report is a single page with sections (Overview, Tech Stack, Architecture, Algorithms, Methodologies, Pattern Rationale, Pitfalls, Glossary, Quiz), with parallel Technical/Layman views and light/dark theme toggle.\n\nTech stack: bash + markdown + html + css + javascript. No build tools. The CSS is a single file (`assets/template.css`) embedded into the final HTML by the launcher.\n\nThe HTML uses these UI elements (UI contracts already drafted in parallel):\n- Sticky TOC (left sidebar on desktop, top dropdown on mobile)\n- Header with brand, view toggle (Technical ↔ Layman), theme toggle (light / dark / auto)\n- Section cards (collapsible) — header with title + collapse toggle\n- Body text in two variants\n- Code blocks (mono)\n- Mermaid diagrams (white-on-dark / dark-on-light needs to work)\n- Tech-stack chips (pill cards per dependency)\n- Glossary list with hover tooltips on terms used elsewhere in the page\n- Quiz cards (interactive — choices, \"check answer\" button, explanation reveal)\n- Pitfall cards with severity color (low/medium/high)\n\n# Your Task\n\nGenerate contract for this Layer 4 component and write to `/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing/.framework/contracts/theme/DesignTokens.contract.md`:\n\n```yaml\ncomponents:\n  - name: DesignTokens\n    responsibility: \"CSS custom properties for the HTML report — color palette (light + dark), typography scale, spacing, radii, shadows, motion\"\n    owns:\n      - assets/template.css\n    key_complexity: \"Readable typographic hierarchy that works in both light and dark, and is calm enough not to compete with code blocks and diagrams\"\n    dependencies: []\n```\n\n# Contract Template (theme)\n\nUse the standard theme template:\n\n```\n# DesignTokens Contract\n\nLayer: theme\n\n## Responsibility\n\n{One sentence}\n\n## Color Tokens\n\n| Token | Light Value | Dark Value | Usage |\n|-------|-------------|------------|-------|\n\n## Typography Tokens\n\n| Token | Font Family | Size | Weight | Line Height | Usage |\n|-------|-------------|------|--------|-------------|-------|\n\n## Spacing Tokens\n\n| Token | Value | Usage |\n|-------|-------|-------|\n\n## Radius Tokens\n\n| Token | Value | Usage |\n|-------|-------|-------|\n\n## Shadow Tokens\n\n| Token | Light | Dark | Usage |\n|-------|-------|------|-------|\n\n## Motion Tokens\n\n| Token | Value | Usage |\n|-------|-------|-------|\n\n## Component Styles\n\n{Pre-built styles using only token references — section card, chip, button, quiz choice, pitfall severity classes, glossary tooltip, TOC item.}\n\n## Test Requirements\n\n- [ ] All tokens resolve in light and dark modes without raw values leaking through\n- [ ] Type scale is readable at 1.5 line-height for body\n- [ ] Color contrast for body text >= WCAG AA (4.5:1)\n- [ ] Code blocks have distinguishable bg from page bg in both modes\n- [ ] Mermaid diagrams render legibly in both modes (set Mermaid theme via JS based on theme)\n```\n\n# Critical Requirements\n\n1. **Token naming**: prefix everything `--waid-` to avoid collision when embedded.\n2. **Color palette**: provide a calm, content-first palette (think doc-site: thoughtbot, Stripe docs, Linear). Avoid neon, avoid heavy saturation. Light mode bg ≈ #fefefe / #fafafa; dark mode bg ≈ #0e1014 / #14171d. Accent color used sparingly.\n3. **Type pair**: a humanist sans for body (e.g., \"Inter, system-ui, -apple-system, Segoe UI, Roboto, sans-serif\") and a mono for code (\"JetBrains Mono, Fira Code, Menlo, Consolas, monospace\"). No font @import — system fonts only, with one tier of fallbacks acceptable. NO CDN font dependency.\n4. **Type scale**: define `--waid-fs-xs` through `--waid-fs-3xl` using a 1.2 ratio.\n5. **Spacing scale**: 4-based: 4, 8, 12, 16, 24, 32, 48, 64.\n6. **Severity colors** for pitfalls: `--waid-color-severity-low/medium/high` mapping to muted green/amber/red, with both light + dark values. Must remain WCAG AA.\n7. **Component styles**: provide complete CSS class definitions (using tokens only) for: `.waid-card`, `.waid-chip`, `.waid-btn`, `.waid-toc-item`, `.waid-quiz-choice`, `.waid-pitfall--low/medium/high`, `.waid-glossary-tooltip`, `.waid-toggle`. Document only — the implementation goes in the build phase.\n8. **Print styles**: brief mention of how the report should print (e.g., expand all sections, hide TOC, hide toggles).\n9. **Reduced motion**: respect `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)` — kill transitions.\n10. **Theme switching**: `data-theme=\"light\"` / `data-theme=\"dark\"` on `<html>`; `data-theme=\"auto\"` defers to `prefers-color-scheme`.\n\n# Deliverables\n\n- `/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing/.framework/contracts/theme/DesignTokens.contract.md`\n\nReport back: file path written, count of color tokens, count of typography tokens, count of component styles defined.","run_in_background":true},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":817,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1449,"cache_read_input_tokens":54691,"output_tokens":11103,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1449,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":817,"output_tokens":11103,"cache_read_input_