{"parentUuid":"cffcb042-7dc6-4c84-a6f6-021dea6ac651","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"591e7a93-1386-4c23-b524-46911cf3d6b9","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01C87Qma63RDM9upNksddDtK","type":"tool_result","content":"120\t| `--waid-space-8` | `32px` | Between major sections |\n121\t| `--waid-space-12` | `48px` | Section vertical rhythm |\n122\t| `--waid-space-16` | `64px` | Page-level vertical padding |\n123\t\n124\t---\n125\t\n126\t## Radius Tokens\n127\t\n128\t| Token | Value | Usage |\n129\t|---|---|---|\n130\t| `--waid-radius-sm` | `4px` | Inline code, small chips, toggle thumb |\n131\t| `--waid-radius-md` | `8px` | Cards, buttons, quiz choices |\n132\t| `--waid-radius-lg` | `12px` | Code blocks, large modal-style surfaces |\n133\t| `--waid-radius-xl` | `16px` | Sidebar panel, hero areas |\n134\t| `--waid-radius-full` | `9999px` | Toggle track, pill chips, focus ring on circular icons |\n135\t\n136\t---\n137\t\n138\t## Shadow Tokens\n139\t\n140\t| Token | Light | Dark | Usage |\n141\t|---|---|---|---|\n142\t| `--waid-shadow-xs` | `0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.06)` | `0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.3)` | Chips, subtle lift |\n143\t| `--waid-shadow-sm` | `0 2px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.08)` | `0 2px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.4)` | Cards at rest |\n144\t| `--waid-shadow-md` | `0 4px 16px rgba(0,0,0,0.10)` | `0 4px 16px rgba(0,0,0,0.5)` | Cards on hover, tooltips |\n145\t| `--waid-shadow-focus` | `0 0 0 3px rgba(59,114,242,0.35)` | `0 0 0 3px rgba(93,143,255,0.4)` | Keyboard focus ring |\n146\t\n147\t---\n148\t\n149\t## Motion Tokens\n150\t\n151\t| Token | Value | Usage |\n152\t|---|---|---|\n153\t| `--waid-duration-instant` | `80ms` | Toggle thumb snap, chip press |\n154\t| `--waid-duration-fast` | `150ms` | Collapse/expand icon rotation, hover state |\n155\t| `--waid-duration-normal` | `240ms` | Card collapse, tooltip fade, theme crossfade |\n156\t| `--waid-duration-slow` | `400ms` | Page-level transitions (reserved) |\n157\t| `--waid-ease-default` | `cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1)` | Standard ease-in-out (Material curve) |\n158\t| `--waid-ease-spring` | `cubic-bezier(0.34, 1.56, 0.64, 1)` | Toggle thumb overshoot |\n159\t\n160\t**Reduced motion override**: Inside `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)` set all `--waid-duration-*` tokens to `0ms` and replace `--waid-ease-spring` with `linear`. Component transitions reference only these tokens, so they go instant automatically — no per-component override needed.\n161\t\n162\t---\n163\t\n164\t## Component Styles\n165\t\n166\tAll class definitions use token references only. No raw color, size, or timing values in component CSS.\n167\t\n168\t### `.waid-card` — Section card (collapsible)\n169\t\n170\t```css\n171\t.waid-card {\n172\t  background: var(--waid-color-bg-surface);\n173\t  border: 1px solid var(--waid-color-border);\n174\t  border-radius: var(--waid-radius-md);\n175\t  box-shadow: var(--waid-shadow-sm);\n176\t  padding: var(--waid-space-6);\n177\t  transition: box-shadow var(--waid-duration-fast) var(--waid-ease-default);\n178\t}\n179\t.waid-card:hover {\n180\t  box-shadow: var(--waid-shadow-md);\n181\t}\n182\t.waid-card__header {\n183\t  display: flex;\n184\t  align-items: center;\n185\t  justify-content: space-between;\n186\t  cursor: pointer;\n187\t  gap: var(--waid-space-2);\n188\t}\n189\t.waid-card__title {\n190\t  font-family: var(--waid-font-sans);\n191\t  font-size: var(--waid-fs-lg);\n192\t  font-weight: var(--waid-fw-semibold);\n193\t  line-height: var(--waid-lh-tight);\n194\t  letter-spacing: var(--waid-ls-tight);\n195\t  color: var(--waid-color-text-primary);\n196\t}\n197\t.waid-card__body {\n198\t  font-family: var(--waid-font-sans);\n199\t  font-size: var(--waid-fs-base);"}]},"uuid":"e1a5e86f-62f5-43c7-8608-a19c33ca3936","timestamp":"2026-05-02T05:55:30.664Z","toolUseResult":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing/.framework/contracts/theme/DesignTokens.contract.md","content":"| `--waid-space-8` | `32px` | Between major sections |\n| `--waid-space-12` | `48px` | Section vertical rhythm |\n| `--waid-space-16` | `64px` | Page-level vertical padding |\n\n---\n\n## Radius Tokens\n\n| Token | Value | Usage |\n|---|---|---|\n| `--waid-radius-sm` | `4px` | Inline code, small chips, toggle thumb |\n| `--waid-radius-md` | `8px` | Cards, buttons, quiz choices |\n| `--waid-radius-lg` | `12px` | Code blocks, large modal-style surfaces |\n| `--waid-radius-xl` | `16px` | Sidebar panel, hero areas |\n| `--waid-radius-full` | `9999px` | Toggle track, pill chips, focus ring on circular icons |\n\n---\n\n## Shadow Tokens\n\n| Token | Light | Dark | Usage |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `--waid-shadow-xs` | `0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.06)` | `0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.3)` | Chips, subtle lift |\n| `--waid-shadow-sm` | `0 2px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.08)` | `0 2px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.4)` | Cards at rest |\n| `--waid-shadow-md` | `0 4px 16px rgba(0,0,0,0.10)` | `0 4px 16px rgba(0,0,0,0.5)` | Cards on hover, tooltips |\n| `--waid-shadow-focus` | `0 0 0 3px rgba(59,114,242,0.35)` | `0 0 0 3px rgba(93,143,255,0.4)` | Keyboard focus ring |\n\n---\n\n## Motion Tokens\n\n| Token | Value | Usage |\n|---|---|---|\n| `--waid-duration-instant` | `80ms` | Toggle thumb snap, chip press |\n| `--waid-duration-fast` | `150ms` | Collapse/expand icon rotation, hover state |\n| `--waid-duration-normal` | `240ms` | Card collapse, tooltip fade, theme crossfade |\n| `--waid-duration-slow` | `400ms` | Page-level transitions (reserved) |\n| `--waid-ease-default` | `cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1)` | Standard ease-in-out (Material curve) |\n| `--waid-ease-spring` | `cubic-bezier(0.34, 1.56, 0.64, 1)` | Toggle thumb overshoot |\n\n**Reduced motion override**: Inside `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)` set all `--waid-duration-*` tokens to `0ms` and replace `--waid-ease-spring` with `linear`. Component transitions reference only these tokens, so they go instant automatically — no per-component override needed.\n\n---\n\n## Component Styles\n\nAll class definitions use token references only. No raw color, size, or timing values in component CSS.\n\n### `.waid-card` — Section card (collapsible)\n\n```css\n.waid-card {\n  background: var(--waid-color-bg-surface);\n  border: 1px solid var(--waid-color-border);\n  border-radius: var(--waid-radius-md);\n  box-shadow: var(--waid-shadow-sm);\n  padding: var(--waid-space-6);\n  transition: box-shadow var(--waid-duration-fast) var(--waid-ease-default);\n}\n.waid-card:hover {\n  box-shadow: var(--waid-shadow-md);\n}\n.waid-card__header {\n  display: flex;\n  align-items: center;\n  justify-content: space-between;\n  cursor: pointer;\n  gap: var(--waid-space-2);\n}\n.waid-card__title {\n  font-family: var(--waid-font-sans);\n  font-size: var(--waid-fs-lg);\n  font-weight: var(--waid-fw-semibold);\n  line-height: var(--waid-lh-tight);\n  letter-spacing: var(--waid-ls-tight);\n  color: var(--waid-color-text-primary);\n}\n.waid-card__body {\n  font-family: var(--waid-font-sans);\n  font-size: var(--waid-fs-base);","numLines":80,"startLine":120,"totalLines":517}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"cffcb042-7dc6-4c84-a6f6-021dea6ac651","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing","sessionId":"72a03414-ba52-4106-b27a-7f28ae50fe45","version":"2.1.126","gitBranch":"main"}
{"parentUuid":"e1a5e86f-62f5-43c7-8608-a19c33ca3936","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_011BMkPnWQpWCYzxyCT5exCW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01XypJXo1cWdvpz3bFrVJeT9","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing/.framework/contracts/ui/InteractiveJS.contract.md","offset":199,"limit":60},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5143,"cache_read_input_tokens":117181,"output_tokens":1849,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5143,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":1849,"cache_read_input_tokens":117181,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5143,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5143},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CadE1gUiu6iJtXmnAj47K","type":"assistant","uuid":"9b46e4c2-4a3e-42a2-9466-72752b60a6eb","timestamp":"2026-05-02T05:55:31.773Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing","sessionId":"72a03414-ba52-4106-b27a-7f28ae50fe45","version":"2.1.126","gitBranch":"main"}
{"parentUuid":"9b46e4c2-4a3e-42a2-9466-72752b60a6eb","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"591e7a93-1386-4c23-b524-46911cf3d6b9","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XypJXo1cWdvpz3bFrVJeT9","type":"tool_result","content":"199\t## Theme Dependency\n200\t\n201\tInteractiveJS reads theme tokens indirectly via the DOM state (`data-waid-theme` on `#waid-root`). It does not read CSS custom property values directly. The one case where a theme value is needed programmatically is Mermaid — it maps `data-waid-theme` to a Mermaid theme string:\n202\t\n203\t| `data-waid-theme` value | Resolved `prefers-color-scheme` | Mermaid theme passed |\n204\t|---|---|---|\n205\t| `light` | (any) | `default` |\n206\t| `dark` | (any) | `dark` |\n207\t| `auto` | `light` | `default` |\n208\t| `auto` | `dark` | `dark` |\n209\t\n210\tResolution is done via `window.matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: dark)').matches`.\n211\t\n212\tThe following tokens are referenced by name in comments within the JS for documentation purposes only (CSS owns the values):\n213\t\n214\t- `--waid-color-correct` — applied via `.waid-quiz-correct` class\n215\t- `--waid-color-wrong` — applied via `.waid-quiz-wrong` class\n216\t- `--waid-duration-fast`, `--waid-duration-medium` — referenced in animation timing comments\n217\t- `--waid-z-tooltip` — applied via `.waid-tooltip` class (CSS sets the z-index)\n218\t\n219\t## Test Requirements\n220\t\n221\t- [ ] `window.WAID` is defined after script evaluation\n222\t- [ ] `window.WAID.init(null)` shows `#waid-error` and does not throw\n223\t- [ ] `window.WAID.init(fixtureJson)` renders all 9 sections with correct content\n224\t- [ ] `window.WAID.init(fixtureJson)` called twice is a no-op on the second call\n225\t- [ ] `setView('layman')` toggles `data-waid-view` on `#waid-root` and fires `waid:view-change`\n226\t- [ ] `setView('layman')` persists to `localStorage['waid-view']`\n227\t- [ ] `setTheme('dark')` sets `data-waid-theme=\"dark\"` on `#waid-root` and fires `waid:theme-change`\n228\t- [ ] `setTheme('dark')` persists to `localStorage['waid-theme']`\n229\t- [ ] All analysis text rendered as `textContent` — injecting `<script>alert(1)</script>` as a field value does not execute\n230\t- [ ] Template cloning: no `innerHTML` calls with user-controlled strings (static analysis / grep check)\n231\t- [ ] Empty `tech_stack: []` results in `data-waid-empty=\"true\"` on the tech-stack section and `.waid-toc-item--empty` on its TOC entry\n232\t- [ ] Mermaid absent from global scope: architecture section shows `.waid-mermaid-fallback` with the raw diagram source, page does not throw\n233\t- [ ] Quiz: correct answer click adds `.waid-quiz-correct`, wrong click adds `.waid-quiz-wrong` and also reveals the correct button\n234\t- [ ] Quiz: all buttons disabled after any choice\n235\t- [ ] Quiz: explanation revealed after choice; active-view explanation matches current view\n236\t- [ ] Glossary tooltip: appears on hover of `.waid-glossary-term`; content matches the active view's definition\n237\t- [ ] localStorage blocked (throws): `init()` completes without error, defaults applied\n238\t- [ ] `waid:ready` event fires on `document` after successful `init()`\n239\t- [ ] Section collapse: clicking `.waid-section-toggle` flips `aria-expanded`; section body collapses; `waid:section-toggle` event fires\n240\t- [ ] Diagram zoom: clicking `#waid-arch-diagram` opens `#waid-diagram-zoom` dialog\n241\t- [ ] `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce` — no JS-driven animation callbacks fire (transitions are CSS-only and are suppressed by the CSS media query)\n242\t"}]},"uuid":"939808ec-baba-4ee4-ae76-8e583697c7ce","timestamp":"2026-05-02T05:55:31.782Z","toolUseResult":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing/.framework/contracts/ui/InteractiveJS.contract.md","content":"## Theme Dependency\n\nInteractiveJS reads theme tokens indirectly via the DOM state (`data-waid-theme` on `#waid-root`). It does not read CSS custom property values directly. The one case where a theme value is needed programmatically is Mermaid — it maps `data-waid-theme` to a Mermaid theme string:\n\n| `data-waid-theme` value | Resolved `prefers-color-scheme` | Mermaid theme passed |\n|---|---|---|\n| `light` | (any) | `default` |\n| `dark` | (any) | `dark` |\n| `auto` | `light` | `default` |\n| `auto` | `dark` | `dark` |\n\nResolution is done via `window.matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: dark)').matches`.\n\nThe following tokens are referenced by name in comments within the JS for documentation purposes only (CSS owns the values):\n\n- `--waid-color-correct` — applied via `.waid-quiz-correct` class\n- `--waid-color-wrong` — applied via `.waid-quiz-wrong` class\n- `--waid-duration-fast`, `--waid-duration-medium` — referenced in animation timing comments\n- `--waid-z-tooltip` — applied via `.waid-tooltip` class (CSS sets the z-index)\n\n## Test Requirements\n\n- [ ] `window.WAID` is defined after script evaluation\n- [ ] `window.WAID.init(null)` shows `#waid-error` and does not throw\n- [ ] `window.WAID.init(fixtureJson)` renders all 9 sections with correct content\n- [ ] `window.WAID.init(fixtureJson)` called twice is a no-op on the second call\n- [ ] `setView('layman')` toggles `data-waid-view` on `#waid-root` and fires `waid:view-change`\n- [ ] `setView('layman')` persists to `localStorage['waid-view']`\n- [ ] `setTheme('dark')` sets `data-waid-theme=\"dark\"` on `#waid-root` and fires `waid:theme-change`\n- [ ] `setTheme('dark')` persists to `localStorage['waid-theme']`\n- [ ] All analysis text rendered as `textContent` — injecting `<script>alert(1)</script>` as a field value does not execute\n- [ ] Template cloning: no `innerHTML` calls with user-controlled strings (static analysis / grep check)\n- [ ] Empty `tech_stack: []` results in `data-waid-empty=\"true\"` on the tech-stack section and `.waid-toc-item--empty` on its TOC entry\n- [ ] Mermaid absent from global scope: architecture section shows `.waid-mermaid-fallback` with the raw diagram source, page does not throw\n- [ ] Quiz: correct answer click adds `.waid-quiz-correct`, wrong click adds `.waid-quiz-wrong` and also reveals the correct button\n- [ ] Quiz: all buttons disabled after any choice\n- [ ] Quiz: explanation revealed after choice; active-view explanation matches current view\n- [ ] Glossary tooltip: appears on hover of `.waid-glossary-term`; content matches the active view's definition\n- [ ] localStorage blocked (throws): `init()` completes without error, defaults applied\n- [ ] `waid:ready` event fires on `document` after successful `init()`\n- [ ] Section collapse: clicking `.waid-section-toggle` flips `aria-expanded`; section body collapses; `waid:section-toggle` event fires\n- [ ] Diagram zoom: clicking `#waid-arch-diagram` opens `#waid-diagram-zoom` dialog\n- [ ] `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce` — no JS-driven animation callbacks fire (transitions are CSS-only and are suppressed by the CSS media query)\n","numLines":44,"startLine":199,"totalLines":242}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"9b46e4c2-4a3e-42a2-9466-72752b60a6eb","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing","sessionId":"72a03414-ba52-4106-b27a-7f28ae50fe45","version":"2.1.126","gitBranch":"main"}
