{"parentUuid":"3f132ff0-3b6c-4cef-a0fd-40a3c5882085","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01EkGxXRZbbGwQ1yzkFRy2eC","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Cleaner fix: drop the 2 extra placeholders from HtmlTemplate (project name + schema version) — the JS can populate `<title>` and meta tags from the embedded JSON itself. Single source of truth."}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4578,"cache_read_input_tokens":135851,"output_tokens":585,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4578,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":585,"cache_read_input_tokens":135851,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4578,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4578},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CadEAbVLZw4mGyJDM9Dq3","type":"assistant","uuid":"5ac42888-276e-4c9d-89f5-5070349e0d31","timestamp":"2026-05-02T05:57:17.553Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing","sessionId":"72a03414-ba52-4106-b27a-7f28ae50fe45","version":"2.1.126","gitBranch":"main"}
{"parentUuid":"5ac42888-276e-4c9d-89f5-5070349e0d31","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01EkGxXRZbbGwQ1yzkFRy2eC","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01E38eZHZC6NHQStTnK4Ap93","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing/.framework/contracts/ui/HtmlTemplate.contract.md","offset":1,"limit":80},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4578,"cache_read_input_tokens":135851,"output_tokens":585,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4578,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":585,"cache_read_input_tokens":135851,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4578,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4578},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CadEAbVLZw4mGyJDM9Dq3","type":"assistant","uuid":"7fe2175a-c968-4cf5-8026-6c218929cf5f","timestamp":"2026-05-02T05:57:19.256Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing","sessionId":"72a03414-ba52-4106-b27a-7f28ae50fe45","version":"2.1.126","gitBranch":"main"}
{"parentUuid":"7fe2175a-c968-4cf5-8026-6c218929cf5f","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"591e7a93-1386-4c23-b524-46911cf3d6b9","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01E38eZHZC6NHQStTnK4Ap93","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# HtmlTemplate Contract\n2\t\n3\tLayer: ui\n4\t\n5\t## Responsibility\n6\t\n7\tSingle self-contained HTML shell — with inline CSS stub and deferred JS — that contains every section template element and chrome (view-toggle, theme-toggle, sticky TOC); the launcher script substitutes placeholder tokens to produce the final deliverable `under-the-hood.html`.\n8\t\n9\t## Substitution / API Contract\n10\t\n11\tThe launcher (`scripts/launch.sh`) performs a literal string substitution pass over `assets/template.html`. Each placeholder is a unique sentinel that will not collide with normal HTML, CSS, or JSON content.\n12\t\n13\t| Placeholder | Location in HTML | Substituted value shape | Failure mode |\n14\t|---|---|---|---|\n15\t| `__WAID_ANALYSIS_JSON__` | Inside `<script id=\"waid-data\" type=\"application/json\">__WAID_ANALYSIS_JSON__</script>` in `<head>` | Valid JSON string conforming to AnalysisSchema (no surrounding quotes; raw JSON object) | If empty/missing: `window.WAID.init` receives `null`; page renders error banner `#waid-error` and hides all section cards |\n16\t| `__WAID_TEMPLATE_CSS__` | Inside `<style id=\"waid-style\">__WAID_TEMPLATE_CSS__</style>` in `<head>` | Full contents of `assets/template.css` (DesignTokens) as raw text | If empty: page renders unstyled but functionally intact |\n17\t| `__WAID_TEMPLATE_JS__` | Inside `<script id=\"waid-script\">__WAID_TEMPLATE_JS__</script>` before `</body>` | Full contents of `assets/template.js` (InteractiveJS) as raw text | If empty: page is static; no interactivity; section content remains hidden (JS is required to call init) |\n18\t| `__WAID_GENERATED_AT__` | `<meta name=\"waid:generated-at\" content=\"__WAID_GENERATED_AT__\">` in `<head>` | ISO-8601 datetime string (e.g. `2026-05-02T14:30:00Z`) — same as `meta.generated_at` in the JSON | If missing: meta tag has empty content; no visible effect |\n19\t| `__WAID_PROJECT_NAME__` | `<title>__WAID_PROJECT_NAME__ — Under the Hood</title>` and `<h1 id=\"waid-title\">` inside `#waid-header` | Plain text project name (HTML-escaped by launcher before substitution) | If missing: title reads \"— Under the Hood\"; h1 is empty |\n20\t| `__WAID_SCHEMA_VERSION__` | `<meta name=\"waid:schema-version\" content=\"__WAID_SCHEMA_VERSION__\">` in `<head>` | Semver string (e.g. `1.0.0`) | If missing: meta tag has empty content |\n21\t\n22\t### Substitution Safety Rules (enforced by launcher, documented here for auditability)\n23\t\n24\t- `__WAID_PROJECT_NAME__` must be HTML-entity-escaped by the launcher before substitution (replace `&`, `<`, `>`, `\"`, `'`).\n25\t- `__WAID_ANALYSIS_JSON__` must NOT be escaped — it is raw JSON inside a `type=\"application/json\"` script element (immune to HTML parser). The launcher must verify the JSON is valid before injecting.\n26\t- `__WAID_TEMPLATE_CSS__` and `__WAID_TEMPLATE_JS__` must NOT contain the literal string `</style>` or `</script>` respectively (they won't; CSS and JS don't naturally contain those). If they do the launcher must escape them.\n27\t- Substitution is performed with a single-pass `sed` or equivalent; placeholders are guaranteed not to appear in the substituted values.\n28\t\n29\t## Visual / Behavior\n30\t\n31\t- **Default state**: On first load (localStorage empty), view defaults to `technical`, theme defaults to `auto` (matches `prefers-color-scheme`). All section cards are expanded. TOC highlights the first entry. The view-toggle switch is in the \"Technical\" position; the theme button shows the current resolved theme icon.\n32\t- **Loading state**: Not applicable for a static file. The one quasi-loading case is Mermaid CDN: the architecture section shows a `<div class=\"waid-mermaid-pending\">Rendering diagram…</div>` placeholder until Mermaid calls back; if Mermaid never loads (CDN failure or offline), the placeholder changes to `class=\"waid-mermaid-fallback\"` with the raw Mermaid source in a `<pre>`.\n33\t- **Empty state**: If a section's array in the JSON is empty (e.g. `quiz: []`) the corresponding `<section data-waid-section=\"quiz\">` receives `data-waid-empty=\"true\"` and the section header shows a `(—)` badge; the section body shows `<p class=\"waid-empty-notice\">No entries available.</p>`. The TOC entry for that section is greyed out (`.waid-toc-item--empty`) but still present and still scrolls to the section.\n34\t- **Error state**:\n35\t  - JSON malformed or null: `#waid-root` gets `data-waid-state=\"error\"`. `#waid-error` banner (hidden by default with `hidden` attribute) becomes visible with message \"Report data could not be loaded.\" All `<section data-waid-section>` elements remain hidden (`hidden` attribute).\n36\t  - Mermaid CDN failure: Architecture section renders the raw Mermaid source in a `<pre class=\"waid-mermaid-fallback\">`. Rest of page unaffected.\n37\t  - Unexpected JS exception during render: `window.onerror` handler surfaces `#waid-error` banner with the error message. Partial renders are left in place.\n38\t- **Animations**: Section collapse/expand: CSS `transition: grid-template-rows 220ms ease`. View toggle: `transition: opacity 120ms ease` on content swap. Theme toggle: `transition: background-color 180ms ease, color 180ms ease` on `:root`. TOC active-item underline: `transition: transform 150ms ease`. No motion when `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce` matches — all transitions set to `0ms`.\n39\t- **Interactions**:\n40\t  - Click TOC entry → smooth-scroll to section (`scroll-behavior: smooth`; JS fallback for browsers that ignore CSS smooth-scroll).\n41\t  - Click section `<header class=\"waid-section-header\">` → toggle collapse; `aria-expanded` flips on the header button; section body `<div class=\"waid-section-body\">` toggles `data-collapsed`.\n42\t  - Hover/focus any `<span class=\"waid-glossary-term\">` → tooltip `<div role=\"tooltip\" class=\"waid-tooltip\">` appears with the layman definition. Tooltip is positioned via JS (IntersectionObserver to keep in viewport).\n43\t  - Click `#waid-view-toggle` → calls `window.WAID.setView(...)`, flips all `[data-waid-view]` content, persists to localStorage.\n44\t  - Click `#waid-theme-toggle` → cycles `auto → light → dark → auto`, calls `window.WAID.setTheme(...)`, persists.\n45\t  - Click quiz choice `<button class=\"waid-quiz-choice\">` → evaluates, adds `.waid-quiz-correct` or `.waid-quiz-wrong`, reveals explanation, locks remaining choices.\n46\t  - Click Mermaid diagram container `#waid-arch-diagram` → opens a `<dialog id=\"waid-diagram-zoom\">` modal with full-size diagram; Escape or backdrop click closes it.\n47\t\n48\t## DOM Structure Contract\n49\t\n50\tThe launcher and InteractiveJS depend on the following IDs / classes / attributes being present and stable in the template:\n51\t\n52\t### Top-level shell\n53\t\n54\t```\n55\t<body id=\"waid-root\" data-waid-theme=\"auto\" data-waid-view=\"technical\" data-waid-state=\"loading\">\n56\t  <div id=\"waid-error\" hidden>…</div>\n57\t  <header id=\"waid-header\">\n58\t    <h1 id=\"waid-title\">__WAID_PROJECT_NAME__ — Under the Hood</h1>\n59\t    <div id=\"waid-controls\">\n60\t      <button id=\"waid-view-toggle\" aria-pressed=\"false\">…</button>\n61\t      <button id=\"waid-theme-toggle\">…</button>\n62\t    </div>\n63\t  </header>\n64\t  <div id=\"waid-layout\">\n65\t    <nav id=\"waid-toc\" aria-label=\"Contents\">\n66\t      <ol id=\"waid-toc-list\"><!-- populated by JS --></ol>\n67\t    </nav>\n68\t    <main id=\"waid-main\">\n69\t      <!-- one <section data-waid-section=\"…\"> per report section -->\n70\t    </main>\n71\t  </div>\n72\t  <dialog id=\"waid-diagram-zoom\">…</dialog>\n73\t</body>\n74\t```\n75\t\n76\t### Section elements (static in HTML; content populated by JS from JSON)\n77\t\n78\tEach section follows this pattern:\n79\t```html\n80\t<section id=\"waid-section-{name}\" data-waid-section=\"{name}\" hidden>"}]},"uuid":"ca5bf3c1-57ae-4617-b473-a4e626b860b2","timestamp":"2026-05-02T05:57:19.276Z","toolUseResult":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing/.framework/contracts/ui/HtmlTemplate.contract.md","content":"# HtmlTemplate Contract\n\nLayer: ui\n\n## Responsibility\n\nSingle self-contained HTML shell — with inline CSS stub and deferred JS — that contains every section template element and chrome (view-toggle, theme-toggle, sticky TOC); the launcher script substitutes placeholder tokens to produce the final deliverable `under-the-hood.html`.\n\n## Substitution / API Contract\n\nThe launcher (`scripts/launch.sh`) performs a literal string substitution pass over `assets/template.html`. Each placeholder is a unique sentinel that will not collide with normal HTML, CSS, or JSON content.\n\n| Placeholder | Location in HTML | Substituted value shape | Failure mode |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `__WAID_ANALYSIS_JSON__` | Inside `<script id=\"waid-data\" type=\"application/json\">__WAID_ANALYSIS_JSON__</script>` in `<head>` | Valid JSON string conforming to AnalysisSchema (no surrounding quotes; raw JSON object) | If empty/missing: `window.WAID.init` receives `null`; page renders error banner `#waid-error` and hides all section cards |\n| `__WAID_TEMPLATE_CSS__` | Inside `<style id=\"waid-style\">__WAID_TEMPLATE_CSS__</style>` in `<head>` | Full contents of `assets/template.css` (DesignTokens) as raw text | If empty: page renders unstyled but functionally intact |\n| `__WAID_TEMPLATE_JS__` | Inside `<script id=\"waid-script\">__WAID_TEMPLATE_JS__</script>` before `</body>` | Full contents of `assets/template.js` (InteractiveJS) as raw text | If empty: page is static; no interactivity; section content remains hidden (JS is required to call init) |\n| `__WAID_GENERATED_AT__` | `<meta name=\"waid:generated-at\" content=\"__WAID_GENERATED_AT__\">` in `<head>` | ISO-8601 datetime string (e.g. `2026-05-02T14:30:00Z`) — same as `meta.generated_at` in the JSON | If missing: meta tag has empty content; no visible effect |\n| `__WAID_PROJECT_NAME__` | `<title>__WAID_PROJECT_NAME__ — Under the Hood</title>` and `<h1 id=\"waid-title\">` inside `#waid-header` | Plain text project name (HTML-escaped by launcher before substitution) | If missing: title reads \"— Under the Hood\"; h1 is empty |\n| `__WAID_SCHEMA_VERSION__` | `<meta name=\"waid:schema-version\" content=\"__WAID_SCHEMA_VERSION__\">` in `<head>` | Semver string (e.g. `1.0.0`) | If missing: meta tag has empty content |\n\n### Substitution Safety Rules (enforced by launcher, documented here for auditability)\n\n- `__WAID_PROJECT_NAME__` must be HTML-entity-escaped by the launcher before substitution (replace `&`, `<`, `>`, `\"`, `'`).\n- `__WAID_ANALYSIS_JSON__` must NOT be escaped — it is raw JSON inside a `type=\"application/json\"` script element (immune to HTML parser). The launcher must verify the JSON is valid before injecting.\n- `__WAID_TEMPLATE_CSS__` and `__WAID_TEMPLATE_JS__` must NOT contain the literal string `</style>` or `</script>` respectively (they won't; CSS and JS don't naturally contain those). If they do the launcher must escape them.\n- Substitution is performed with a single-pass `sed` or equivalent; placeholders are guaranteed not to appear in the substituted values.\n\n## Visual / Behavior\n\n- **Default state**: On first load (localStorage empty), view defaults to `technical`, theme defaults to `auto` (matches `prefers-color-scheme`). All section cards are expanded. TOC highlights the first entry. The view-toggle switch is in the \"Technical\" position; the theme button shows the current resolved theme icon.\n- **Loading state**: Not applicable for a static file. The one quasi-loading case is Mermaid CDN: the architecture section shows a `<div class=\"waid-mermaid-pending\">Rendering diagram…</div>` placeholder until Mermaid calls back; if Mermaid never loads (CDN failure or offline), the placeholder changes to `class=\"waid-mermaid-fallback\"` with the raw Mermaid source in a `<pre>`.\n- **Empty state**: If a section's array in the JSON is empty (e.g. `quiz: []`) the corresponding `<section data-waid-section=\"quiz\">` receives `data-waid-empty=\"true\"` and the section header shows a `(—)` badge; the section body shows `<p class=\"waid-empty-notice\">No entries available.</p>`. The TOC entry for that section is greyed out (`.waid-toc-item--empty`) but still present and still scrolls to the section.\n- **Error state**:\n  - JSON malformed or null: `#waid-root` gets `data-waid-state=\"error\"`. `#waid-error` banner (hidden by default with `hidden` attribute) becomes visible with message \"Report data could not be loaded.\" All `<section data-waid-section>` elements remain hidden (`hidden` attribute).\n  - Mermaid CDN failure: Architecture section renders the raw Mermaid source in a `<pre class=\"waid-mermaid-fallback\">`. Rest of page unaffected.\n  - Unexpected JS exception during render: `window.onerror` handler surfaces `#waid-error` banner with the error message. Partial renders are left in place.\n- **Animations**: Section collapse/expand: CSS `transition: grid-template-rows 220ms ease`. View toggle: `transition: opacity 120ms ease` on content swap. Theme toggle: `transition: background-color 180ms ease, color 180ms ease` on `:root`. TOC active-item underline: `transition: transform 150ms ease`. No motion when `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce` matches — all transitions set to `0ms`.\n- **Interactions**:\n  - Click TOC entry → smooth-scroll to section (`scroll-behavior: smooth`; JS fallback for browsers that ignore CSS smooth-scroll).\n  - Click section `<header class=\"waid-section-header\">` → toggle collapse; `aria-expanded` flips on the header button; section body `<div class=\"waid-section-body\">` toggles `data-collapsed`.\n  - Hover/focus any `<span class=\"waid-glossary-term\">` → tooltip `<div role=\"tooltip\" class=\"waid-tooltip\">` appears with the layman definition. Tooltip is positioned via JS (IntersectionObserver to keep in viewport).\n  - Click `#waid-view-toggle` → calls `window.WAID.setView(...)`, flips all `[data-waid-view]` content, persists to localStorage.\n  - Click `#waid-theme-toggle` → cycles `auto → light → dark → auto`, calls `window.WAID.setTheme(...)`, persists.\n  - Click quiz choice `<button class=\"waid-quiz-choice\">` → evaluates, adds `.waid-quiz-correct` or `.waid-quiz-wrong`, reveals explanation, locks remaining choices.\n  - Click Mermaid diagram container `#waid-arch-diagram` → opens a `<dialog id=\"waid-diagram-zoom\">` modal with full-size diagram; Escape or backdrop click closes it.\n\n## DOM Structure Contract\n\nThe launcher and InteractiveJS depend on the following IDs / classes / attributes being present and stable in the template:\n\n### Top-level shell\n\n```\n<body id=\"waid-root\" data-waid-theme=\"auto\" data-waid-view=\"technical\" data-waid-state=\"loading\">\n  <div id=\"waid-error\" hidden>…</div>\n  <header id=\"waid-header\">\n    <h1 id=\"waid-title\">__WAID_PROJECT_NAME__ — Under the Hood</h1>\n    <div id=\"waid-controls\">\n      <button id=\"waid-view-toggle\" aria-pressed=\"false\">…</button>\n      <button id=\"waid-theme-toggle\">…</button>\n    </div>\n  </header>\n  <div id=\"waid-layout\">\n    <nav id=\"waid-toc\" aria-label=\"Contents\">\n      <ol id=\"waid-toc-list\"><!-- populated by JS --></ol>\n    </nav>\n    <main id=\"waid-main\">\n      <!-- one <section data-waid-section=\"…\"> per report section -->\n    </main>\n  </div>\n  <dialog id=\"waid-diagram-zoom\">…</dialog>\n</body>\n```\n\n### Section elements (static in HTML; content populated by JS from JSON)\n\nEach section follows this pattern:\n```html\n<section id=\"waid-section-{name}\" data-waid-section=\"{name}\" hidden>","numLines":80,"startLine":1,"totalLines":231}},"sourceToolAssistantUU