{"parentUuid":"39e175f3-d030-480c-8e5a-fbf7b6f90bc0","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01HcuGtaNMercEArxEZDowWb","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01T3VvXGn6zL5cvM5XXeTfBb","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing/.framework/contracts/ui/InteractiveJS.contract.md","offset":1,"limit":75},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1918,"cache_read_input_tokens":144223,"output_tokens":353,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1918,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":353,"cache_read_input_tokens":144223,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1918,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1918},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CadECd8cQ36DhTYnLLFs9","type":"assistant","uuid":"7fdf7497-6fe2-449c-bf07-6b476bdbaf57","timestamp":"2026-05-02T05:57:43.255Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing","sessionId":"72a03414-ba52-4106-b27a-7f28ae50fe45","version":"2.1.126","gitBranch":"main"}
{"parentUuid":"7fdf7497-6fe2-449c-bf07-6b476bdbaf57","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"591e7a93-1386-4c23-b524-46911cf3d6b9","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01T3VvXGn6zL5cvM5XXeTfBb","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# InteractiveJS Contract\n2\t\n3\tLayer: ui\n4\t\n5\t## Responsibility\n6\t\n7\tInline JavaScript module — embedded by HtmlTemplate inside `<script id=\"waid-script\">` — that reads the substituted analysis JSON, renders it into the DOM via `<template>` cloning, and wires all interactive behaviors: view toggle, theme toggle, TOC scroll-spy, glossary tooltips, section collapse, Mermaid hydration, quiz logic, and diagram zoom.\n8\t\n9\t## Substitution / API Contract\n10\t\n11\tInteractiveJS is a plain JavaScript file (`assets/template.js`). It ships as raw source; the launcher injects it verbatim. It must work without any module bundler, transpiler, or `import` / `require` — vanilla ES2020 is the target (no top-level `await`; no ES modules syntax unless the `<script>` tag carries `type=\"module\"`, which it does not by default).\n12\t\n13\t### Global Object: `window.WAID`\n14\t\n15\tAll public entry points are properties of a single namespace object assigned during script evaluation:\n16\t\n17\t```js\n18\twindow.WAID = {\n19\t  init(analysisJson),        // primary entry — call once after DOM ready\n20\t  setView(view),             // 'technical' | 'layman'\n21\t  setTheme(theme),           // 'light' | 'dark' | 'auto'\n22\t  getState(),                // returns { view, theme, collapsedSections: Set }\n23\t};\n24\t```\n25\t\n26\t#### `window.WAID.init(analysisJson)`\n27\t\n28\t| Concern | Spec |\n29\t|---|---|\n30\t| Idempotent | Yes — if called a second time it is a no-op (guard on `_initialized` flag). |\n31\t| Input | Parsed JS object conforming to AnalysisSchema, or `null`. |\n32\t| Null / invalid input | Sets `document.getElementById('waid-root').dataset.waidState = 'error'`; removes `hidden` from `#waid-error`; returns early. |\n33\t| Execution order | 1. Validate input. 2. Restore view + theme from localStorage. 3. Render each section. 4. Build TOC. 5. Wire all event listeners. 6. Start scroll-spy. 7. Hydrate Mermaid (async). 8. Set `data-waid-state=\"ready\"` on `#waid-root`. |\n34\t| Self-invocation | The script reads `<script id=\"waid-data\" type=\"application/json\">` on `DOMContentLoaded` and calls `window.WAID.init(parsed)` automatically. Consumers may also call it manually (useful in tests). |\n35\t\n36\t#### `window.WAID.setView(view)`\n37\t\n38\t| Concern | Spec |\n39\t|---|---|\n40\t| Accepted values | `'technical'`, `'layman'` |\n41\t| Invalid value | Logs console warning; no-op. |\n42\t| DOM effect | Sets `document.getElementById('waid-root').dataset.waidView = view`; updates `aria-pressed` on `#waid-view-toggle`. CSS rules handle visibility of `[data-waid-view]` elements. |\n43\t| Persistence | `localStorage.setItem('waid-view', view)` |\n44\t| Custom event | Dispatches `CustomEvent('waid:view-change', { detail: { view } })` on `document`. |\n45\t\n46\t#### `window.WAID.setTheme(theme)`\n47\t\n48\t| Concern | Spec |\n49\t|---|---|\n50\t| Accepted values | `'light'`, `'dark'`, `'auto'` |\n51\t| Invalid value | Logs console warning; no-op. |\n52\t| DOM effect | Sets `document.getElementById('waid-root').dataset.waidTheme = theme`. CSS uses `[data-waid-theme]` + `@media (prefers-color-scheme)` for resolution. |\n53\t| Persistence | `localStorage.setItem('waid-theme', theme)` |\n54\t| Custom event | Dispatches `CustomEvent('waid:theme-change', { detail: { theme } })` on `document`. |\n55\t\n56\t### localStorage Keys\n57\t\n58\t| Key | Values | Default |\n59\t|---|---|---|\n60\t| `waid-view` | `'technical'` \\| `'layman'` | `'technical'` |\n61\t| `waid-theme` | `'light'` \\| `'dark'` \\| `'auto'` | `'auto'` |\n62\t\n63\tIf `localStorage` throws (private browsing with storage blocked), the script catches and continues with in-memory defaults — no crash.\n64\t\n65\t### Custom DOM Events (emitted on `document`)\n66\t\n67\t| Event name | Detail shape | When fired |\n68\t|---|---|---|\n69\t| `waid:view-change` | `{ view: 'technical' \\| 'layman' }` | After view toggle |\n70\t| `waid:theme-change` | `{ detail: { theme: 'light' \\| 'dark' \\| 'auto' } }` | After theme toggle |\n71\t| `waid:section-toggle` | `{ sectionName: string, expanded: boolean }` | After collapse/expand |\n72\t| `waid:quiz-answer` | `{ questionIndex: number, correct: boolean }` | After user selects a quiz choice |\n73\t| `waid:ready` | `{}` | After `init()` completes successfully |\n74\t\n75\t### Required DOM Contract"}]},"uuid":"75ccbd4c-79bd-4674-8b32-bf80857173cc","timestamp":"2026-05-02T05:57:43.273Z","toolUseResult":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing/.framework/contracts/ui/InteractiveJS.contract.md","content":"# InteractiveJS Contract\n\nLayer: ui\n\n## Responsibility\n\nInline JavaScript module — embedded by HtmlTemplate inside `<script id=\"waid-script\">` — that reads the substituted analysis JSON, renders it into the DOM via `<template>` cloning, and wires all interactive behaviors: view toggle, theme toggle, TOC scroll-spy, glossary tooltips, section collapse, Mermaid hydration, quiz logic, and diagram zoom.\n\n## Substitution / API Contract\n\nInteractiveJS is a plain JavaScript file (`assets/template.js`). It ships as raw source; the launcher injects it verbatim. It must work without any module bundler, transpiler, or `import` / `require` — vanilla ES2020 is the target (no top-level `await`; no ES modules syntax unless the `<script>` tag carries `type=\"module\"`, which it does not by default).\n\n### Global Object: `window.WAID`\n\nAll public entry points are properties of a single namespace object assigned during script evaluation:\n\n```js\nwindow.WAID = {\n  init(analysisJson),        // primary entry — call once after DOM ready\n  setView(view),             // 'technical' | 'layman'\n  setTheme(theme),           // 'light' | 'dark' | 'auto'\n  getState(),                // returns { view, theme, collapsedSections: Set }\n};\n```\n\n#### `window.WAID.init(analysisJson)`\n\n| Concern | Spec |\n|---|---|\n| Idempotent | Yes — if called a second time it is a no-op (guard on `_initialized` flag). |\n| Input | Parsed JS object conforming to AnalysisSchema, or `null`. |\n| Null / invalid input | Sets `document.getElementById('waid-root').dataset.waidState = 'error'`; removes `hidden` from `#waid-error`; returns early. |\n| Execution order | 1. Validate input. 2. Restore view + theme from localStorage. 3. Render each section. 4. Build TOC. 5. Wire all event listeners. 6. Start scroll-spy. 7. Hydrate Mermaid (async). 8. Set `data-waid-state=\"ready\"` on `#waid-root`. |\n| Self-invocation | The script reads `<script id=\"waid-data\" type=\"application/json\">` on `DOMContentLoaded` and calls `window.WAID.init(parsed)` automatically. Consumers may also call it manually (useful in tests). |\n\n#### `window.WAID.setView(view)`\n\n| Concern | Spec |\n|---|---|\n| Accepted values | `'technical'`, `'layman'` |\n| Invalid value | Logs console warning; no-op. |\n| DOM effect | Sets `document.getElementById('waid-root').dataset.waidView = view`; updates `aria-pressed` on `#waid-view-toggle`. CSS rules handle visibility of `[data-waid-view]` elements. |\n| Persistence | `localStorage.setItem('waid-view', view)` |\n| Custom event | Dispatches `CustomEvent('waid:view-change', { detail: { view } })` on `document`. |\n\n#### `window.WAID.setTheme(theme)`\n\n| Concern | Spec |\n|---|---|\n| Accepted values | `'light'`, `'dark'`, `'auto'` |\n| Invalid value | Logs console warning; no-op. |\n| DOM effect | Sets `document.getElementById('waid-root').dataset.waidTheme = theme`. CSS uses `[data-waid-theme]` + `@media (prefers-color-scheme)` for resolution. |\n| Persistence | `localStorage.setItem('waid-theme', theme)` |\n| Custom event | Dispatches `CustomEvent('waid:theme-change', { detail: { theme } })` on `document`. |\n\n### localStorage Keys\n\n| Key | Values | Default |\n|---|---|---|\n| `waid-view` | `'technical'` \\| `'layman'` | `'technical'` |\n| `waid-theme` | `'light'` \\| `'dark'` \\| `'auto'` | `'auto'` |\n\nIf `localStorage` throws (private browsing with storage blocked), the script catches and continues with in-memory defaults — no crash.\n\n### Custom DOM Events (emitted on `document`)\n\n| Event name | Detail shape | When fired |\n|---|---|---|\n| `waid:view-change` | `{ view: 'technical' \\| 'layman' }` | After view toggle |\n| `waid:theme-change` | `{ detail: { theme: 'light' \\| 'dark' \\| 'auto' } }` | After theme toggle |\n| `waid:section-toggle` | `{ sectionName: string, expanded: boolean }` | After collapse/expand |\n| `waid:quiz-answer` | `{ questionIndex: number, correct: boolean }` | After user selects a quiz choice |\n| `waid:ready` | `{}` | After `init()` completes successfully |\n\n### Required DOM Contract","numLines":75,"startLine":1,"totalLines":242}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"7fdf7497-6fe2-449c-bf07-6b476bdbaf57","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing","sessionId":"72a03414-ba52-4106-b27a-7f28ae50fe45","version":"2.1.126","gitBranch":"main"}
