{"parentUuid":"8e851dda-8995-4e16-a5e0-99c5a19c298f","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"5cadac53-c33f-4865-a5d7-489ac2a83b72","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01B4cNscobqmWvHB4wzQJzKE","type":"tool_result","content":"# Phase 3: Application Skeleton\n\n**Goal**: Build the runnable application shell with placeholder slots where components will be inserted. The skeleton defines layout, navigation, and screen composition — but contains no real components.\n\n## Step 1: Detect stack & dispatch language pack\n\nRead `.framework/state.json` (written by Discover/Launch) to find `primary_language` and `frameworks`. Then look for a matching language pack in this order:\n\n1. For each entry in `state.frameworks` (most specific first), check `~/.claude/frameworks/trellis/languages/<framework>/init.sh`\n2. Else check `~/.claude/frameworks/trellis/languages/<primary_language>/init.sh`\n3. Else fall back to the **manual process** below\n\n```bash\nPACK=\"\"\nfor f in $(python3 -c 'import json; s=json.load(open(\".framework/state.json\")); print(\" \".join(s.get(\"frameworks\",[])+([s[\"primary_language\"]] if s.get(\"primary_language\") else [])))'); do\n  if [ -x ~/.claude/frameworks/trellis/languages/\"$f\"/init.sh ]; then\n    PACK=\"$f\"; break\n  fi\ndone\necho \"Pack: ${PACK:-<none — using manual process>}\"\n```\n\nIf `PACK` is set, run it:\n\n```bash\n~/.claude/frameworks/trellis/languages/\"$PACK\"/init.sh \"{project_dir}\" \"{app_name}\" \"{org}\" \"{extra_args}\"\n```\n\nEach pack ships its own argument shape (Flutter takes `<platforms>`; others vary — read the pack's `init.sh` header). The pack handles project creation, dependency install, screen skeletons, router/shell, and any required codegen in one command. After it completes you only need to:\n\n1. Verify the skeleton compiles (run the pack's `analyze-errors.sh` if present, otherwise the project's lint/build command from `state.json`)\n2. Fix any issues the pack didn't handle (custom dependencies, theme details)\n3. Generate the assembly manifest (Step 4 below)\n4. Commit\n\nIf the pack documentation flags any post-init step (e.g., codegen), confirm it ran. See **Pack-specific notes** below.\n\n### Pack-specific notes\n\n#### Flutter\n\nThe Flutter pack runs `build_runner` automatically if `build_runner` is in the deps. **This is critical: codegen must run before Phase 4**, otherwise agents will write code against types that don't exist yet, causing hundreds of errors that only surface in Phase 6.\n\nIf you added deps manually after `init.sh` ran, re-run codegen before committing:\n```bash\ndart run build_runner build --delete-conflicting-outputs\n```\n\n(Add a subsection here as new packs land. See `~/.claude/frameworks/trellis/languages/README.md` for the pack contract.)\n\n---\n\n## Manual Process (when no pack matches)\n\n### Step 1: Initialize Project\n\nIf not already done:\n\n1. Initialize git repo (`git init`)\n2. Set up project boilerplate based on tech stack from `.framework/plan.md`:\n   - Package manifest (`package.json` / `pubspec.yaml` / `pyproject.toml` / `Cargo.toml` / `go.mod` / etc.)\n   - Install core dependencies via the stack's package manager\n   - Configure testing framework\n   - Create basic directory structure\n\n**Important:** When writing to files that already exist (e.g., a `main.*` created by a project generator), always Read the file first before using Write. The Write tool requires files to be read before overwriting.\n\n### Step 2: Build Screen / Module Skeletons\n\nFor each screen (or top-level module / route handler / command, for non-UI projects) in `.framework/plan.md`, create a file with:\n\n1. **Layout structure** — how panels/sections (or routes/handlers) are arranged\n2. **SLOT markers** — one per component that will be inserted\n\nSlot convention (use the stack's comment syntax — `//`, `#`, etc.):\n\n```\n// SLOT: {component_name} — {ComponentType} goes here\n[Placeholder element sized to approximate the real component]\n```\n\n**When creating multiple files**, use Agent sub-agents to parallelize:\n- Group into batches of 3-4\n- Dispatch agents with `model: \"sonnet\"` to write each batch\n- Each agent gets the file list, slot conventions, and tech stack info\n\n### Step 3: Build Navigation / Composition Shell\n\nCreate the app shell with:\n- Navigation structure (sidebar, tab bar, top nav, route table — whatever fits the app)\n- Route definitions pointing to screen / handler skeletons\n- App entry point that wires the router and shell together\n\nFor non-UI stacks: the equivalent is a top-level `main`/`app` that wires the router/dispatcher to the handler skeletons.\n\n### Step 4: Generate Assembly Manifest\n\nRead `.framework/templates/assembly-manifest.yaml` for the structure. Fill in based on `.framework/plan.md`:\n\n- Each screen's slots and which component fills each slot\n- Where props come from (which state provider / store / service, which field)\n- Where callbacks go (which method on which provider/service)\n- Conditional visibility rules\n- Provider / store / service initialization (app-level vs screen-level)\n- Assembly order (simplest to most complex)\n\nWrite to `.framework/assembly_manifest.yaml`.\n\n---\n\n## Final Steps (both pack and manual)\n\n### Verify Skeleton\n\n- [ ] Project compiles without errors (use `state.json.lint_command` or the pack's `analyze-errors.sh`)\n- [ ] Navigation between screens / routes works\n- [ ] All slots are marked with comments\n- [ ] Assembly manifest matches `.framework/plan.md`'s screens and components\n\nFix any compilation errors before proceeding.\n\n### Commit and Update Progress\n\n1. Commit everything to main: `feat: application skeleton with slot placeholders`\n2. Update `.framework/progress.md`:\n   - Set current phase to 3, status to complete\n   - Add Phase 3 to history\n\n**The skeleton MUST be committed to main before Phase 4**, because worktrees branch from HEAD.\n\n## Completion Gate\n\n- [ ] Skeleton compiles and runs showing placeholders\n- [ ] Every screen/module has SLOT markers for all its components\n- [ ] `.framework/assembly_manifest.yaml` exists and is complete\n- [ ] Everything committed to main branch\n- [ ] `.framework/progress.md` updated","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"b1f0290e-4303-4e19-b9ce-c6702db8b782","timestamp":"2026-05-02T06:10:31.245Z","toolUseResult":{"stdout":"# Phase 3: Application Skeleton\n\n**Goal**: Build the runnable application shell with placeholder slots where components will be inserted. The skeleton defines layout, navigation, and screen composition — but contains no real components.\n\n## Step 1: Detect stack & dispatch language pack\n\nRead `.framework/state.json` (written by Discover/Launch) to find `primary_language` and `frameworks`. Then look for a matching language pack in this order:\n\n1. For each entry in `state.frameworks` (most specific first), check `~/.claude/frameworks/trellis/languages/<framework>/init.sh`\n2. Else check `~/.claude/frameworks/trellis/languages/<primary_language>/init.sh`\n3. Else fall back to the **manual process** below\n\n```bash\nPACK=\"\"\nfor f in $(python3 -c 'import json; s=json.load(open(\".framework/state.json\")); print(\" \".join(s.get(\"frameworks\",[])+([s[\"primary_language\"]] if s.get(\"primary_language\") else [])))'); do\n  if [ -x ~/.claude/frameworks/trellis/languages/\"$f\"/init.sh ]; then\n    PACK=\"$f\"; break\n  fi\ndone\necho \"Pack: ${PACK:-<none — using manual process>}\"\n```\n\nIf `PACK` is set, run it:\n\n```bash\n~/.claude/frameworks/trellis/languages/\"$PACK\"/init.sh \"{project_dir}\" \"{app_name}\" \"{org}\" \"{extra_args}\"\n```\n\nEach pack ships its own argument shape (Flutter takes `<platforms>`; others vary — read the pack's `init.sh` header). The pack handles project creation, dependency install, screen skeletons, router/shell, and any required codegen in one command. After it completes you only need to:\n\n1. Verify the skeleton compiles (run the pack's `analyze-errors.sh` if present, otherwise the project's lint/build command from `state.json`)\n2. Fix any issues the pack didn't handle (custom dependencies, theme details)\n3. Generate the assembly manifest (Step 4 below)\n4. Commit\n\nIf the pack documentation flags any post-init step (e.g., codegen), confirm it ran. See **Pack-specific notes** below.\n\n### Pack-specific notes\n\n#### Flutter\n\nThe Flutter pack runs `build_runner` automatically if `build_runner` is in the deps. **This is critical: codegen must run before Phase 4**, otherwise agents will write code against types that don't exist yet, causing hundreds of errors that only surface in Phase 6.\n\nIf you added deps manually after `init.sh` ran, re-run codegen before committing:\n```bash\ndart run build_runner build --delete-conflicting-outputs\n```\n\n(Add a subsection here as new packs land. See `~/.claude/frameworks/trellis/languages/README.md` for the pack contract.)\n\n---\n\n## Manual Process (when no pack matches)\n\n### Step 1: Initialize Project\n\nIf not already done:\n\n1. Initialize git repo (`git init`)\n2. Set up project boilerplate based on tech stack from `.framework/plan.md`:\n   - Package manifest (`package.json` / `pubspec.yaml` / `pyproject.toml` / `Cargo.toml` / `go.mod` / etc.)\n   - Install core dependencies via the stack's package manager\n   - Configure testing framework\n   - Create basic directory structure\n\n**Important:** When writing to files that already exist (e.g., a `main.*` created by a project generator), always Read the file first before using Write. The Write tool requires files to be read before overwriting.\n\n### Step 2: Build Screen / Module Skeletons\n\nFor each screen (or top-level module / route handler / command, for non-UI projects) in `.framework/plan.md`, create a file with:\n\n1. **Layout structure** — how panels/sections (or routes/handlers) are arranged\n2. **SLOT markers** — one per component that will be inserted\n\nSlot convention (use the stack's comment syntax — `//`, `#`, etc.):\n\n```\n// SLOT: {component_name} — {ComponentType} goes here\n[Placeholder element sized to approximate the real component]\n```\n\n**When creating multiple files**, use Agent sub-agents to parallelize:\n- Group into batches of 3-4\n- Dispatch agents with `model: \"sonnet\"` to write each batch\n- Each agent gets the file list, slot conventions, and tech stack info\n\n### Step 3: Build Navigation / Composition Shell\n\nCreate the app shell with:\n- Navigation structure (sidebar, tab bar, top nav, route table — whatever fits the app)\n- Route definitions pointing to screen / handler skeletons\n- App entry point that wires the router and shell together\n\nFor non-UI stacks: the equivalent is a top-level `main`/`app` that wires the router/dispatcher to the handler skeletons.\n\n### Step 4: Generate Assembly Manifest\n\nRead `.framework/templates/assembly-manifest.yaml` for the structure. Fill in based on `.framework/plan.md`:\n\n- Each screen's slots and which component fills each slot\n- Where props come from (which state provider / store / service, which field)\n- Where callbacks go (which method on which provider/service)\n- Conditional visibility rules\n- Provider / store / service initialization (app-level vs screen-level)\n- Assembly order (simplest to most complex)\n\nWrite to `.framework/assembly_manifest.yaml`.\n\n---\n\n## Final Steps (both pack and manual)\n\n### Verify Skeleton\n\n- [ ] Project compiles without errors (use `state.json.lint_command` or the pack's `analyze-errors.sh`)\n- [ ] Navigation between screens / routes works\n- [ ] All slots are marked with comments\n- [ ] Assembly manifest matches `.framework/plan.md`'s screens and components\n\nFix any compilation errors before proceeding.\n\n### Commit and Update Progress\n\n1. Commit everything to main: `feat: application skeleton with slot placeholders`\n2. Update `.framework/progress.md`:\n   - Set current phase to 3, status to complete\n   - Add Phase 3 to history\n\n**The skeleton MUST be committed to main before Phase 4**, because worktrees branch from HEAD.\n\n## Completion Gate\n\n- [ ] Skeleton compiles and runs showing placeholders\n- [ ] Every screen/module has SLOT markers for all its components\n- [ ] `.framework/assembly_manifest.yaml` exists and is complete\n- [ ] Everything committed to main branch\n- [ ] `.framework/progress.md` updated","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"8e851dda-8995-4e16-a5e0-99c5a19c298f","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing","sessionId":"72a03414-ba52-4106-b27a-7f28ae50fe45","version":"2.1.126","gitBranch":"main"}
