{"parentUuid":"ff7553c1-86c8-46cb-919f-4c2792ed0bdc","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01FA6TTkQ3ftBAenyvA4y269","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_015jt9VznDhfLHAPmtjDjHdW","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cat ~/.claude/frameworks/trellis/framework/phase4-parallel-build.md 2>&1 | head -150","description":"Read Phase 4 instructions"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2112,"cache_read_input_tokens":174604,"output_tokens":444,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2112,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":444,"cache_read_input_tokens":174604,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2112,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2112},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CadGmvW2zxyQPUBP9asWm","type":"assistant","uuid":"505f0261-90d5-4cc5-a253-047d71f51a8c","timestamp":"2026-05-02T06:31:27.645Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing/waid-commands","sessionId":"72a03414-ba52-4106-b27a-7f28ae50fe45","version":"2.1.126","gitBranch":"main"}
{"parentUuid":"505f0261-90d5-4cc5-a253-047d71f51a8c","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"5cadac53-c33f-4865-a5d7-489ac2a83b72","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015jt9VznDhfLHAPmtjDjHdW","type":"tool_result","content":"# Phase 4: Parallel Component Build\n\n**Goal**: Dispatch specialized agents to build all components in parallel tiers.\n\n## Tier Execution Model\n\n```\nTIER 1 — No dependencies (maximum parallelism)\n├── Data Agent(s)    → All Layer 1 components\n├── UI Agent(s)      → All Layer 2 components\n└── Theme Agent      → All Layer 4 components\n\nTIER 2 — Depends on Tier 1\n└── Logic Agent(s)   → All Layer 3 components (can import L1 data stores)\n\nTIER 3 — Depends on everything\n└── Assembler        → Phase 5 (separate phase)\n```\n\n## Pre-Step A: Bundle Contracts\n\nBefore dispatching agents, bundle contracts per layer for efficient reading:\n\n```bash\npython3 ~/.claude/frameworks/trellis/bundle-contracts.py \".framework/contracts\" \".framework/contracts\"\n```\n\nThis produces one file per layer:\n- `.framework/contracts/contracts-data.bundle.md`\n- `.framework/contracts/contracts-ui.bundle.md`\n- `.framework/contracts/contracts-logic.bundle.md`\n- `.framework/contracts/contracts-theme.bundle.md`\n\nEach bundle is a single file containing all contracts for that layer — much easier for agents to consume than reading 10+ individual files.\n\n## Pre-Step B: Generate Stubs with Haiku\n\n**This is the single biggest token-saving step.** Before build agents start, use cheap Haiku agents to generate code stubs from contracts. Stubs contain the correct structure — imports, class declarations, method signatures, constructors, type definitions — but with empty method bodies (`// TODO: implement` or `throw UnimplementedError()`).\n\n**Why this matters:**\n- Stubs are ~30% of each file (imports, signatures, class boilerplate)\n- Build agents generate ~70% less output (only method bodies)\n- Stubs compile — validating that contracts are consistent before any real code is written\n- Stubs give build agents a starting point — they use Edit to fill in bodies, not Write to create entire files\n\n**Dispatch stub generators — ALL layers in parallel, using Haiku:**\n\n```\nAgent tool:\n  description: \"Generate {layer} stubs from contracts\"\n  model: \"haiku\"\n  prompt: |\n    Read the contract bundle at .framework/contracts/contracts-{layer}.bundle.md\n    \n    For each contract, generate a stub file with:\n    - All imports needed for the types referenced in the contract\n    - Class/function declarations matching the contract's API surface exactly\n    - Method signatures with correct parameter types and return types\n    - Empty method bodies: throw UnimplementedError('{methodName} not yet implemented')\n    - For test files: test group structure with empty test bodies\n    \n    Tech stack: {language}, {framework}, {testing_framework}\n    \n    Write stubs using multiple Write calls per turn (batch 5-8 per message).\n    Implementation files go in the project's established directory structure.\n    Test stubs go in the corresponding test directory.\n    \n    Do NOT implement any logic. Only signatures and structure.\n  run_in_background: true\n```\n\n**Dispatch ALL 4 layer stub generators in a single message.** They're independent and Haiku is fast — all 4 should complete in 2-3 minutes.\n\nAfter stubs are generated:\n1. Run the analyzer/linter once to verify stubs compile\n2. Fix any import or type issues (these reveal contract inconsistencies cheaply)\n3. Commit stubs — **stage by name, not `git add -A`**. Stub generators reported the directories they wrote to:\n   ```bash\n   # Stage exactly the layer directories the stub agents populated.\n   # Example for a Flutter feature tree (adjust to project's layout):\n   git add lib/features/*/data/ lib/features/*/presentation/widgets/ \\\n           lib/core/theme/ lib/features/*/domain/ lib/features/*/presentation/providers/ \\\n           test/\n   git status --short\n   git diff --staged --stat\n   ```\n   Show the user the staged list and ask: *\"About to commit stubs with message `chore: add component stubs from contracts`. Proceed? (yes/no)\"*. Only after \"yes\":\n   ```bash\n   git commit -m \"chore: add component stubs from contracts\"\n   ```\n\n**The stubs MUST be committed before dispatching build agents**, so agents start with compilable stub files.\n\n## Process\n\n### Step 1: Read Agent Assignments\n\nRead `.framework/plan.md` → \"Build Tiers\" YAML block (use `.framework/plan-index.md` for the exact line range). This defines:\n- Which agents exist\n- Which components each agent builds\n\n### Step 2: Prepare Agent Prompts\n\nRead `.framework/templates/agent-prompt.md` for the prompt template.\n\nFor EACH agent, compose a prompt containing:\n- `{agent_name}` — from the tier config\n- `{layer}` — data, ui, logic, or theme\n- `{language}`, `{framework}`, `{testing_framework}` — from tech stack in `.framework/plan.md`\n- **Contract instructions** — tell the agent to read its bundle file:\n  > Read your contracts from `.framework/contracts/contracts-{layer}.bundle.md`.\n  > This file contains all contracts for your layer. Implement each one exactly as specified.\n- **Stub instructions** — tell the agent stubs already exist:\n  > Stub files already exist for your components with correct signatures.\n  > Use Edit (not Write) to fill in method bodies. Do not change signatures.\n  > Read each stub file first, then Edit to replace the TODO/UnimplementedError bodies.\n\n**Do NOT try to inline contract text in the agent prompt.** Contracts are too large for that. Agents read their bundle file from disk.\n\n### Step 3: Dispatch Tier 1 Agents\n\n**Dispatch ALL Tier 1 agents in a SINGLE message** for maximum concurrency.\n\n**Model assignment per agent type:**\n\n| Agent | Model | Why |\n|-------|-------|-----|\n| Theme agent | **haiku** | Mechanical — color values, spacing scales, token definitions |\n| Data agents | **sonnet** | Moderate — schemas, DAOs, models with type relationships |\n| UI agents | **sonnet** | Moderate — widgets from clear prop/callback contracts |\n| Logic agents | **sonnet** | Moderate — state machines, services with defined interfaces |\n| Post-build verification | **haiku** | Mechanical — run analyzer, check files exist |\n\nTry `isolation: \"worktree\"` first. If worktree fails (common error: \"Cannot create agent worktree\"), fall back immediately to `run_in_background: true` without isolation:\n\n```\nAttempt 1 (preferred — isolated):\n  Agent tool:\n    description: \"Build {layer} components\"\n    model: \"sonnet\"  # or \"haiku\" for theme\n    prompt: {composed prompt}\n    isolation: \"worktree\"\n\nIf worktree fails → Attempt 2 (fallback — background, no isolation):\n  Agent tool:\n    description: \"Build {layer} components\"\n    model: \"sonnet\"  # or \"haiku\" for theme\n    prompt: {composed prompt}\n    run_in_background: true\n```","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"5e978424-a2fe-4b58-94f6-f02475679bb1","timestamp":"2026-05-02T06:31:28.031Z","toolUseResult":{"stdout":"# Phase 4: Parallel Component Build\n\n**Goal**: Dispatch specialized agents to build all components in parallel tiers.\n\n## Tier Execution Model\n\n```\nTIER 1 — No dependencies (maximum parallelism)\n├── Data Agent(s)    → All Layer 1 components\n├── UI Agent(s)      → All Layer 2 components\n└── Theme Agent      → All Layer 4 components\n\nTIER 2 — Depends on Tier 1\n└── Logic Agent(s)   → All Layer 3 components (can import L1 data stores)\n\nTIER 3 — Depends on everything\n└── Assembler        → Phase 5 (separate phase)\n```\n\n## Pre-Step A: Bundle Contracts\n\nBefore dispatching agents, bundle contracts per layer for efficient reading:\n\n```bash\npython3 ~/.claude/frameworks/trellis/bundle-contracts.py \".framework/contracts\" \".framework/contracts\"\n```\n\nThis produces one file per layer:\n- `.framework/contracts/contracts-data.bundle.md`\n- `.fra