{"parentUuid":"faa60422-70f9-4d9e-b7ff-81b7ff0c0574","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_017juCFLT25GgZJjpsotqa7Y","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Bundles ready. Dispatching tier 1 build agents in parallel (data + ui + theme). Tier 2 (logic) follows once they finish."}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1314,"cache_read_input_tokens":180183,"output_tokens":7998,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1314,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":7998,"cache_read_input_tokens":180183,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1314,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1314},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CadHmJzixPhCuJnzk8JDP","type":"assistant","uuid":"b1d00dc7-2c1d-454d-a1e8-86ae97731c33","timestamp":"2026-05-02T06:44:23.548Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing/waid-commands","sessionId":"72a03414-ba52-4106-b27a-7f28ae50fe45","version":"2.1.126","gitBranch":"main"}
{"parentUuid":"b1d00dc7-2c1d-454d-a1e8-86ae97731c33","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_017juCFLT25GgZJjpsotqa7Y","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01RGQBdadsFhVuSR7p5w8Fp5","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Build L1 data components","subagent_type":"general-purpose","model":"sonnet","prompt":"You are the Trellis Phase 4 data-agent for the `waid-commands` Claude Code plugin. Your job: replace the Phase 3 stubs with full implementations of the Layer 1 (Data) components, exactly per their contracts.\n\n# Read first\n\n1. Your contract bundle: `/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing/.framework/contracts/contracts-data.bundle.md` — contains the full contracts for `AnalysisSchema` and `StackDetectionRules`.\n2. Existing skeleton stubs you must replace (use Read first, then Write):\n   - `/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing/waid-commands/schema/analysis.schema.json`\n   - `/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing/waid-commands/schema/stack-detection.json`\n   - `/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing/waid-commands/schema/README.md` (improve to reflect final shape)\n\n# Tech stack\n\nbash + json + javascript. No build tools. No type system. JSON Schema draft 2020-12.\n\n# What to do\n\n## File 1: `waid-commands/schema/analysis.schema.json`\n\nImplement the FULL `ProjectAnalysis` JSON Schema exactly per the AnalysisSchema contract — every field, every required/optional flag, every nested type, every `$defs` entry, every description string, every enum, `additionalProperties: false` throughout, `quiz.choices` with `minItems: 2, maxItems: 6`, `pitfalls.entries` with `minItems: 1`, etc. The contract bundle contains the canonical schema in its \"JSON Schema Definition\" section — copy it faithfully.\n\nThe skeleton currently has only `{\"$schemaVersion\": {\"const\": 1}}`. Replace the entire file with the full schema.\n\nAfter writing, verify with: `python3 -c \"import json; print('ok' if json.load(open('waid-commands/schema/analysis.schema.json'))['title'] == 'ProjectAnalysis' else 'FAIL')\"`\n\n## File 2: `waid-commands/schema/stack-detection.json`\n\nImplement the FULL stack-detection rules content exactly per the StackDetectionRules contract — all 11 entries (flutter, rust, go, nodejs, python, java, ruby, php, dotnet, swift, unknown) in the order shown in the contract's \"Actual Rules Content\" section.\n\nImportant contract details to honor:\n- The schema field on each entry: `id`, `humanName`, `manifestFiles`, `keyConfigFiles`, `entryPointHints`, optional `workspaceIndicators`, optional `notes`.\n- The `dotnet` entry must include `\"manifestFilesAreGlobs\": true` (this is the resolution for `*.csproj` glob handling).\n- The `unknown` entry must be last and have `\"manifestFiles\": []`.\n- The `nodejs` entry's `keyConfigFiles` is the largest list — include every entry shown in the contract.\n- Top-level `$schemaVersion: 1`.\n\nAfter writing, verify with: `python3 -c \"import json; d=json.load(open('waid-commands/schema/stack-detection.json')); ids=[s['id'] for s in d['stacks']]; print('ok' if all(x in ids for x in ['nodejs','python','rust','go','flutter','java','ruby','php','dotnet','swift','unknown']) else 'FAIL')\"`\n\n## File 3: `waid-commands/schema/README.md`\n\nReplace the brief skeleton with a real README that:\n- Documents the purpose of each schema file\n- Shows the top-level shape of `analysis.schema.json` (a tree of section names)\n- Shows the list of supported stack ids and their `humanName`s\n- States the versioning policy (when to bump `$schemaVersion`)\n- Notes that these files are read by the SlashCommand at run time and must not be modified by users\n\nKeep it under 100 lines. No emojis.\n\n# Important constraints\n\n- Use the Write tool to replace each file (NOT Edit, since the contents change too significantly). Read each file first to satisfy the Write-after-Read requirement.\n- Do not implement any other components — only the 3 files above.\n- Do not add new fields, types, or stacks beyond what the contracts specify.\n- Match the contract's wording in `description` fields verbatim where the contract supplies one. The descriptions become hints for Claude when it produces analysis JSON, so fidelity matters.\n\n# Report back\n\n- File paths written and their sizes\n- Result of the two verify commands above\n- Any contract ambiguities you encountered and how you resolved them","run_in_background":true},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1314,"cache_read_input_tokens":180183,"output_tokens":7998,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1314,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":7998,"cache_read_input_tokens":180183,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1314,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1314},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CadHmJzixPhCuJnzk8JDP","type":"assistant","uuid":"2d92f5a5-29ae-4d12-84fb-263455f8dcb7","timestamp":"2026-05-02T06:44:48.943Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing/waid-commands","sessionId":"72a03414-ba52-4106-b27a-7f28ae50fe45","version":"2.1.126","gitBranch":"main"}
