{"parentUuid":"41f0ddc6-1642-4e91-a9a3-1cb6c1fd666e","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_017juCFLT25GgZJjpsotqa7Y","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01PXuwP4hMp8qM6xh8Ua4tDN","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Build L2 UI components","subagent_type":"general-purpose","model":"sonnet","prompt":"You are the Trellis Phase 4 ui-agent for the `waid-commands` Claude Code plugin. Your job: replace the Phase 3 stubs with full implementations of the Layer 2 (UI) components, exactly per their contracts.\n\n# Read first\n\n1. Your contract bundle: `/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing/.framework/contracts/contracts-ui.bundle.md` — contains the full contracts for `HtmlTemplate` and `InteractiveJS`.\n2. Theme contract bundle (read this for canonical CSS token names you must reference): `/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing/.framework/contracts/contracts-theme.bundle.md`. The theme-agent is building the actual CSS file in parallel; you only NEED the canonical token names. Use only token names listed in that contract.\n3. Data contract bundle (for the analysis JSON shape you must render): `/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing/.framework/contracts/contracts-data.bundle.md`.\n4. Existing skeleton stubs you must replace (use Read first, then Write):\n   - `/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing/waid-commands/assets/template.html`\n   - `/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing/waid-commands/assets/template.js`\n\n# Tech stack\n\nHTML5 + vanilla ES2020 JS. No bundler, no transpiler, no framework. Mermaid loaded from CDN with a graceful fallback.\n\n# What to do\n\n## File 1: `waid-commands/assets/template.html`\n\nImplement the full HTML shell exactly per the HtmlTemplate contract:\n\n- Four placeholders only: `__WAID_ANALYSIS_JSON__`, `__WAID_TEMPLATE_CSS__`, `__WAID_TEMPLATE_JS__`, `__WAID_GENERATED_AT__`. (Project name and schema version come from the embedded JSON, populated by JS — NOT placeholders.)\n- All required IDs from the DOM Structure Contract section: `#waid-root`, `#waid-error`, `#waid-header`, `#waid-title`, `#waid-controls`, `#waid-view-toggle`, `#waid-theme-toggle`, `#waid-layout`, `#waid-toc`, `#waid-toc-list`, `#waid-main`, `#waid-diagram-zoom`, `#waid-templates`, plus `#waid-arch-diagram` inside the architecture section.\n- One `<section data-waid-section=\"{name}\">` per report section: overview, tech-stack, architecture, algorithms, methodologies, pattern-rationale, pitfalls, glossary, quiz. Each has `id=\"waid-section-{name}\"`, a header with `aria-expanded` toggle, and `#waid-section-body-{name}` body.\n- Hidden `<template id=\"tpl-...\">` elements inside `#waid-templates` for: tpl-toc-item, tpl-tech-stack-entry, tpl-algo-entry, tpl-method-entry, tpl-pattern-entry, tpl-pitfall-entry, tpl-glossary-entry, tpl-quiz-entry, tpl-quiz-choice. Each template defines the markup that JS clones for each item.\n- View-conditional content uses `[data-waid-view=\"technical\"]` / `[data-waid-view=\"layman\"]` attribute selectors — show/hide is CSS-only.\n- Mermaid CDN script loaded with `defer`, src `https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/mermaid/dist/mermaid.min.js`.\n- `<title>` defaults to `Under the Hood` (JS overwrites with `${analysis.projectName} — Under the Hood`).\n- `<h1 id=\"waid-title\">` defaults to `Under the Hood` (JS overwrites).\n- Print stylesheet section with `@media print` hiding `#waid-toc`, `#waid-controls`.\n- Sticky `<style id=\"waid-style\">__WAID_TEMPLATE_CSS__</style>` in `<head>`.\n- `<script id=\"waid-data\" type=\"application/json\">__WAID_ANALYSIS_JSON__</script>` in `<head>`.\n- `<script id=\"waid-script\">__WAID_TEMPLATE_JS__</script>` immediately before `</body>`.\n- No inline event handlers (all wiring in JS). No external CSS or JS dependencies except Mermaid CDN.\n- `<meta charset=\"UTF-8\">` and `<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\">` present.\n- `lang=\"en\"` on `<html>`.\n- `data-waid-theme=\"auto\"`, `data-waid-view=\"technical\"`, `data-waid-state=\"loading\"` on `<body id=\"waid-root\">`.\n\nThe file must be valid HTML5 (no unclosed tags, no missing required attributes).\n\n## File 2: `waid-commands/assets/template.js`\n\nImplement the full vanilla-JS module exactly per the InteractiveJS contract. Key points:\n\n- Wrap the entire file in an IIFE: `(function () { 'use strict'; ... })();`\n- Expose `window.WAID = { init, setView, setTheme, getState, _initialized }`.\n- `init(analysisJson)` is idempotent (guard via `_initialized` flag).\n- On `DOMContentLoaded`, parse `JSON.parse(document.getElementById('waid-data').textContent)` and call `init(parsed)`. If parse fails, call `init(null)`.\n- `init(null)` shows `#waid-error`, sets `data-waid-state=\"error\"`, returns.\n- Init sequence: validate → restore localStorage → populate chrome (`document.title`, `#waid-title.textContent`, schema-version meta) → render each section by template-cloning → build TOC → wire listeners → start scroll-spy → hydrate Mermaid (async) → set `data-waid-state=\"ready\"` → fire `waid:ready`.\n- Section rendering uses `<template>` cloning with `textContent` only (NO `innerHTML` on user-controlled strings).\n- `setView('technical' | 'layman')`: updates `data-waid-view`, persists `localStorage['waid-view']`, fires `waid:view-change`. Invalid value: `console.warn` + return.\n- `setTheme('light' | 'dark' | 'auto')`: updates `data-waid-theme`, persists `localStorage['waid-theme']`, fires `waid:theme-change`. Invalid value: `console.warn` + return.\n- localStorage wrapped in try/catch (private browsing tolerance).\n- Glossary tooltips: hover/focus on `.waid-glossary-term` reveals `<div role=\"tooltip\" class=\"waid-glossary-tooltip\">` positioned to stay in viewport.\n- Quiz: click `.waid-quiz-choice` button → evaluate `answerIndex` (clamp + warn if out of bounds) → add `.waid-quiz-correct` or `.waid-quiz-