{"parentUuid":"bcb7ef72-ea37-44c1-9411-45b2a9898488","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_017juCFLT25GgZJjpsotqa7Y","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Q3YETcBYRWBkkaRsREEM76","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Build L4 theme component","subagent_type":"general-purpose","model":"haiku","prompt":"You are the Trellis Phase 4 theme-agent for the `waid-commands` Claude Code plugin. Your job: replace the Phase 3 CSS stub with the full DesignTokens implementation, exactly per the contract.\n\n# Read first\n\n1. Your contract bundle: `/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing/.framework/contracts/contracts-theme.bundle.md` — contains the full DesignTokens contract.\n2. Existing skeleton stub to replace (use Read first, then Write):\n   - `/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing/waid-commands/assets/template.css`\n\n# Tech stack\n\nPlain CSS. No preprocessor. The file is inlined into `<style id=\"waid-style\">` by the launcher, so it MUST NOT contain the literal string `</style>`. No `@import`. No CDN font loads. System fonts only.\n\n# What to do\n\nImplement `assets/template.css` with the FULL token set defined in the DesignTokens contract:\n\n1. **`:root` light-mode tokens** — all 32 color tokens, 23 typography tokens (2 font families, 8 size scale `--waid-fs-xs` through `--waid-fs-3xl` at 1.2 ratio with rem values, 4 weights, 4 line heights, 3 letter-spacings), 8 spacing tokens (`--waid-space-1` through `--waid-space-16` on a 4-px grid), 2 layout tokens (`--waid-content-max-width: 880px`, `--waid-toc-width: 260px`), 4 z-index tokens (header 100, toc 90, tooltip 200, dialog 300), 6 radius tokens (sm 4, md 8, lg 12, xl 16, full 9999, pill 9999), 5 shadow tokens (xs/sm/md/lg/focus) plus 3 semantic alias shadows (`--waid-shadow-card`, `-tooltip`, `-dialog`), 5 motion duration tokens plus the `--waid-duration-normal` alias and 2 ease tokens.\n\n2. **`[data-theme=\"dark\"]` overrides** — every color token that has a different dark value gets overridden here. Use the exact hex/rgb values from the contract.\n\n3. **`[data-theme=\"auto\"]`** — wraps a `@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark)` block that mirrors the dark overrides.\n\n4. **`@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)`** — set every `--waid-duration-*` token to `0ms` and replace `--waid-ease-spring` with `linear`.\n\n5. **Component styles** for: `.waid-card` (with `.waid-card__header`, `.waid-card__title`, `.waid-card__body`, collapsed state via `[data-collapsed]`), `.waid-chip`, `.waid-btn` (with `--primary` and `--ghost` variants), `.waid-toc-item` (with `--active` and `--empty` modifiers), `.waid-quiz-choice` (with `.waid-quiz-correct` and `.waid-quiz-wrong` states), `.waid-pitfall--low/medium/high` (using severity tokens), `.waid-glossary-tooltip` (with `.waid-glossary-term` wrapper), `.waid-toggle` (track + thumb + `.waid-toggle__option--active`).\n\n6. **Global styles**:\n   - Box-sizing: border-box on `*, *::before, *::after`.\n   - `html, body` reset margins, set font-family `var(--waid-font-sans)`, base size, line-height `var(--waid-lh-body)`, color `var(--waid-color-text-primary)`, background `var(--waid-color-bg-base)`.\n   - Headings (h1-h4) typography stack using token references only.\n   - Code blocks (`pre`, `code`) use `var(--waid-font-mono)`, `var(--waid-color-code-bg)`, `var(--waid-color-text-code)`.\n   - Sticky header `#waid-header` and TOC `#waid-toc` use respective z-index tokens and a backdrop-filter for legibility.\n   - View-toggle hides/shows content via `[data-waid-view=\"technical\"] [data-waid-view=\"layman\"] { display: none }` and vice-versa.\n   - Empty section styling: `[data-waid-empty=\"true\"]` reduces opacity of the section body.\n\n7. **Layout grid**:\n   - Mobile-first single-column main below 960px.\n   - At `>= 960px`, two-column layout with `#waid-toc` (260px) on the left and `#waid-main` (max-width 880px) on the right.\n   - Sticky positions: `#waid-header` top: 0; `#waid-toc` top: 64px (below header).\n\n8. **Print stylesheet (`@media print`)**:\n   - Hide `#waid-toc`, `#waid-controls`.\n   - Force light-mode colors (white background, black text).\n   - Expand all collapsed sections (override `[data-collapsed]`).\n   - Page-break-inside: avoid on `.waid-card` and `.waid-pitfall`.\n\n9. **Focus styles**: `:focus-visible` outline using `--waid-shadow-focus` and `--waid-color-focus-ring` for keyboard navigation.\n\n10. **Banner for `data-waid-state=\"error\"`**: `#waid-error` styled as a top-of-page red banner using severity-high tokens.\n\n# Constraints\n\n- Use the Write tool to replace the file (Read first).\n- Reference tokens only — NEVER hard-code a color, font size, or duration in component styles. Top-level token definitions in `:root` and theme overrides are the only places literals appear.\n- Strict naming per contract: prefix every custom property with `--waid-`.\n- File should be 400-700 lines (well-organized). One section per concern, separated by `/* === Section Name === */` headers.\n- Must NOT contain `</style>`.\n- No emojis in CSS comments.\n\n# Verification\n\nAfter writing, verify:\n```\nnode -e \"const fs=require('fs'); const css=fs.readFileSync('/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing/waid-commands/assets/template.css','utf8'); if (css.includes('</style>')) throw new Error('contains </style> sentinel'); const tokens = css.match(/--waid-[a-z0-9-]+/g) || []; const uniq = new Set(tokens); console.log('css ok, '+uniq.size+' unique tokens, '+css.length+' bytes');\"\n```\n\nYou should see at least 75 unique tokens.\n\n# Report back\n\n- File path and line count\n- Output of the verification command\n- Total token count by family (colors, typography, spacing, etc.)\n- Any contract ambiguities","run_in_background":true},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1