{"parentUuid":"7be9e9ed-a7de-40ea-88a6-9d8e1d58ea1b","isSidechain":false,"attachment":{"type":"edited_text_file","filename":"/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing/waid-commands/schema/README.md","snippet":"1\t# Schema Files\n2\t\n3\tStatic JSON files read by the SlashCommand at run time to guide project analysis\n4\tand validate Claude's output. Do not modify these files directly — changes are\n5\ta contract change and must go through the Trellis Phase 7 process.\n6\t\n7\t---\n8\t\n9\t## analysis.schema.json\n10\t\n11\tDefines the canonical shape of the `ProjectAnalysis` JSON document that Claude\n12\tmust emit when the `/under-the-hood` command runs.\n13\t\n14\t**Top-level structure:**\n15\t\n16\t```\n17\tProjectAnalysis\n18\t├── $schemaVersion        integer, const 1\n19\t├── projectName           string\n20\t├── generatedAt           string (ISO-8601 UTC)\n21\t├── detectedStack         string (humanName from StackDetectionRules, or \"Unknown\")\n22\t├── overview              DualSection { technical, layman }\n23\t├── tech_stack\n24\t│   ├── technical         string\n25\t│   ├── layman            string\n26\t│   └── entries[]         { name, role, version }  (minItems: 1)\n27\t├── architecture\n28\t│   ├── technical         string\n29\t│   ├── layman            string\n30\t│   └── mermaid           string (Mermaid source, or \"\" when unavailable)\n31\t├── algorithms\n32\t│   ├── technical         string\n33\t│   ├── layman            string\n34\t│   └── entries[]         { name, technical, layman }  (may be empty)\n35\t├── methodologies\n36\t│   ├── technical         string\n37\t│   ├── layman            string\n38\t│   └── entries[]         { name, technical, layman }\n39\t├── pattern_rationale\n40\t│   ├── technical         string\n41\t│   ├── layman            string\n42\t│   └── entries[]         { pattern, rationale_technical, rationale_layman }\n43\t├── pitfalls\n44\t│   ├── technical         string\n45\t│   ├── layman            string\n46\t│   └── entries[]         { title, severity, technical, layman }  (minItems: 1)\n47\t│       severity enum: \"low\" | \"medium\" | \"high\"\n48\t├── glossary[]            { term, layman, technical? }  (may be empty)\n49\t└── quiz[]                { question, choices[2-6], answerIndex, explanation_layman,\n50\t                            explanation_technical }  (may be empty)\n51\t```\n52\t\n53\tEvery section except `overview` includes both `technical` (power-user) and\n54\t`layman` (plain-English) text so the HTML report can switch views without a\n55\tnetwork round-trip. `additionalProperties: false` is set throughout.\n56\t\n57\t---\n58\t\n59\t## stack-detection.json\n60\t\n61\tAn ordered list of stack detection rules. The SlashCommand iterates these in\n62\torder, matching manifest files found in the project. The first full match sets\n63\t`detectedStack`; all matches contribute to `tech_stack.entries`.\n64\t\n65\t**Supported stacks (in detection priority order):**\n66\t\n67\t| id       | humanName                 |\n68\t|----------|---------------------------|\n69\t| flutter  | Flutter / Dart            |\n70\t| rust     | Rust                      |\n71\t| go       | Go                        |\n72\t| nodejs   | Node.js / JavaScript      |\n73\t| python   | Python                    |\n74\t| java     | Java / JVM                |\n75\t| ruby     | Ruby                      |\n76\t| php      | PHP                       |\n77\t| dotnet   | .NET / C#                 |\n78\t| swift    | Swift / Apple Platforms   |\n79\t| unknown  | Unknown                   |\n80\t\n81\tThe `unknown` entry is always last. It has an empty `manifestFiles` array and\n82\tserves as the fallback when no other manifest is found.\n83\t\n84\tThe `dotnet` entry sets `\"manifestFilesAreGlobs\": true` because its manifest\n85\tfilenames are glob patterns (`*.csproj`, `*.fsproj`, `*.vbproj`).\n86\t\n87\t---\n88\t\n89\t## Versioning policy\n90\t\n91\tBoth files carry `\"$schemaVersion\": 1` at the top level.\n92\t\n93\t- **Do not increment** for purely additive changes (new optional fields, new\n94\t  stack entries with the same rule shape).\n95\t- **Increment** when the shape of an existing field changes in a\n96\t  backward-incompatible way (rename, type change, removal).\n97\t- The HTML renderer displays a warning banner when the embedded analysis JSON\n98\t  carries a `$schemaVersion` that does not equal 1.\n99\t\n100\t---\n101\t\n102\t## Important\n103\t\n104\tThese files are read by the SlashCommand at run time and must not be modified\n105\tby end users. Edits require a corresponding contract update in\n106\t`.framework/contracts/data/` and a Phase 7 refinement cycle."},"type":"attachment","uuid":"62197510-9665-4895-b1ec-463b744b18de","timestamp":"2026-05-02T06:47:09.510Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing/waid-commands","sessionId":"72a03414-ba52-4106-b27a-7f28ae50fe45","version":"2.1.126","gitBranch":"main"}
{"parentUuid":"62197510-9665-4895-b1ec-463b744b18de","isSidechain":false,"attachment":{"type":"edited_text_file","filename":"/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing/waid-commands/schema/stack-detection.json","snippet":"1\t{\n2\t  \"$schemaVersion\": 1,\n3\t  \"stacks\": [\n4\t    {\n5\t      \"id\": \"flutter\",\n6\t      \"humanName\": \"Flutter / Dart\",\n7\t      \"manifestFiles\": [\"pubspec.yaml\"],\n8\t      \"keyConfigFiles\": [\n9\t        \"analysis_options.yaml\",\n10\t        \"dart_test.yaml\",\n11\t        \".flutter-plugins\",\n12\t        \"flutter_launcher_icons.yaml\"\n13\t      ],\n14\t      \"entryPointHints\": [\"lib/main.dart\", \"lib/app.dart\"],\n15\t      \"workspaceIndicators\": [\"melos.yaml\", \"packages/\"],\n16\t      \"notes\": \"pubspec.yaml is unique to Dart/Flutter. Check for flutter: key inside to confirm Flutter (vs pure Dart).\"\n17\t    },\n18\t    {\n19\t      \"id\": \"rust\",\n20\t      \"humanName\": \"Rust\",\n21\t      \"manifestFiles\": [\"Cargo.toml\"],\n22\t      \"keyConfigFiles\": [\n23\t        \"Cargo.lock\",\n24\t        \"rust-toolchain.toml\",\n25\t        \"rust-toolchain\",\n26\t        \".cargo/config.toml\",\n27\t        \"clippy.toml\",\n28\t        \".rustfmt.toml\"\n29\t      ],\n30\t      \"entryPointHints\": [\"src/main.rs\", \"src/lib.rs\"],\n31\t      \"workspaceIndicators\": [\"Cargo.toml\"],\n32\t      \"notes\": \"Cargo.toml may contain [workspace] for monorepos. Check members field.\"\n33\t    },\n34\t    {\n35\t      \"id\": \"go\",\n36\t      \"humanName\": \"Go\",\n37\t      \"manifestFiles\": [\"go.mod\"],\n38\t      \"keyConfigFiles\": [\n39\t        \"go.sum\",\n40\t        \".golangci.yml\",\n41\t        \".golangci.yaml\",\n42\t        \"Makefile\"\n43\t      ],\n44\t      \"entryPointHints\": [\"main.go\", \"cmd/main.go\", \"cmd/*/main.go\"],\n45\t      \"workspaceIndicators\": [\"go.work\"],\n46\t      \"notes\": \"go.work indicates a Go workspace (multi-module monorepo).\"\